title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl pour all dressing.
Mix well.
Let stand about 30 minutes and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Add rice, onion and celery.
Mix soups and Cheez Whiz.
Pour over broccoli and rice mixture.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: baskin robbin pie
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: pineapple diet pie
directions: Mix in bowl, crushed pineapple (juice and all) and add sour cream.
Mix together.
Then add pudding; mix well with top ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until translucent.
Add vegetables, chicken stock, salt and pepper.
Simmer 1/2 hour or longer, until potato is tender.
Puree in food processor or blender.
Serve hot or cold.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and molasses, soda and ginger.
Add beaten egg.
Add flour until you have a dough ready to roll.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 350°.

title: orange blossom punch
directions: Mix juices and water together.
Add approximately 1 liter ginger ale or 7-Up to each bowl of punch just before serving. Serves around 150.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Mix sugar, salt, water, syrup and peanuts together in a 10-inch skillet.
Bring to a good boil and cook until the peanuts and syrup turn a light brown.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Mix well. Pour onto greased cookie sheet to cool.
Remove from pan and break into pieces.
Store in a sealed or airtight container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for hours.
Mix together and put on topping after baking.

title: turkey bake
directions: Layer half of bread in ungreased baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch). Mix turkey, onion, green pepper, pimento, salt and sage.
Spread over bread. Top with remaining bread.
Beat eggs and mayo.
Stir in milk and soup.
Pour on bread.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 325° uncovered until casserole is set and top is golden (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Take out a few minutes before done.
Top with cheese. Return to oven to melt cheese.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix and set aside.

title: three tomato tart
directions: Prepare pastry for single crust, place in a 10-inch tart pan. Trim pastry even with rim of pan.
Do not prick.
Line pastry shell with a double thickness of foil.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Remove foil, bake 7 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven.
Reduce temperature to 325°.

title: fried dill pickles
directions: Mix 1 cup of pancake mix with milk.
Add a dash of salt and pepper, Worcestershire sauce and a touch of Tabasco.
Mix thoroughly until the mix pours easily from a spoon.
Pat pickle chips dry.
Dip pickles in batter, then into cooking oil (400°). Brown pickles on both sides; drain and serve.

title: chicken livers
directions: Slice bacon strip into thirds.
Cut livers into 1 inch pieces. Marinate livers in French dressing and garlic salt for 15 mins.
Place liver in 1 piece of bacon with a slice of chestnut. Wrap up and secure with toothpick. Place on a wire rack sprayed with Pam.
Place another pan under grill to catch bacon drippings. Bake at 400° until bacon is crispy, usually 35-45 mins.

title: barbecued pork steak
directions: Heat all ingredients in a saucepan on the stove, except for pork chops.
Put pork chops on barbecued grill, and brush on the mix.
Cook until done.
Really good tasting.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Scald milk.
Mix dry ingredients together. Add scalded milk, stirring constantly.

Cook in double boiler until smooth and thick, about 15 minutes. Beat egg yolks slightly and add small amount of hot mixture to them. Add this quickly to remainder of hot mixture and cook about 3 minutes more.
Add butter and vanilla. When partly cool, slice bananas into pie shell. Cover with filling and serve with sweetened whipped cream.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar and butter until crumbly. Press 1/2 of crumbs in 9-inch pie pan.
Cover with rhubarb. Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla together.
Cook until thick and clear.
Pour over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by large spoonfuls into small amount of hot oil.
Smooth down with back of spoon.
Brown on both sides.
Top with oleo, sour cream or salsa.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Place beets and juice in pan.
Add vinegar, sugar, water and salt.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Cool to room temperature.

title: cinnamon ornament
directions: Mix glue and applesauce together.
Add dry ingredients.
Knead by hand.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Add a small hole in top by using a small straw.
Allow to dry (about a day).
Add ribbon and hang.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and caramels.
Cook slowly until caramels are dissolved.
Increase heat and cook until soft ball.
Add chocolate bits and peanut butter.

title: chewy-gooey treats
directions: Freeze rolls of cookie dough; slice one roll into 40 (1/8-inch) slices.
Arrange cookie slices in a well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Press cookie dough together to form bottom crust.
Set aside.

title: baskin robbins pie
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Press in bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° until brown (30 minutes).
Cool. Cream together cream cheese, 1/2 Cool Whip and sugar.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top off with rest of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans. Refrigerate.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Wash and cook potatoes (do not peel) until done, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Drain.
Hard-boil eggs.
Chop celery, onions and olives.
Peel potatoes and eggs and cut into medium size pieces. Mix in celery, onions and olives.
Sprinkle in celery seed as you are doing this.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and mustard together, then mix into potato mixture.

title: zucchini pineapple nut bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla together.
Add the zucchini and pineapple.
Combine the dry ingredients and add to the zucchini mixture, mixing well.
Add nuts and raisins and blend. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes in the pan, then turn onto racks.

title: honey chicken
directions: Heat first 5 ingredients, stirring until margarine melts. Pour over chicken arranged in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Turn chicken, sprinkle with paprika and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Mix and let set overnight.
Start baking in cold oven.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: hungarian chicken
directions: For pepper, you may use pepper juice or white pepper before cooking or coarse ground pepper after cooking.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add mayonnaise, water and vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 (8-inch) layers.

title: poke cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, water and the oil in a large mixing bowl; blend well.
Then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes. Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until tests done.
Cool in pan about 15 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cut apples in eighths; spread in well-greased dish.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in fat until coarse like cornmeal.
Sprinkle mixture.
Bake at 350° until fruit is soft and crumbs are brown.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients in the blender.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan (which already has crust in it).
Freeze.
This is a very delicious treat.

title: homestyle cornbread
directions: Mix everything together (in order for best results).
Preheat oven to 400°.
Get skillet
very hot.
Put 1 to 2 Tbsp. of oil in skillet.
Pour in mixture and cook for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: having fun with dough
directions: Mix everything together except 2 cups of the flour.
Let stand 20 minutes in warm place.
Add rest of flour and let rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Roll dough out on a lightly floured board.
Cut in rounds; dip in butter and fold over.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients into a ball.
Roll in 3 tablespoons parsley flakes and 2 teaspoons Italian seasoning.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Slice chicken breasts 1/3 of an inch.
Put it in a deep container.
Add soy sauce, ground pepper and lemon juice. Marinate for an hour.
In a frying pan, put oil.
Wait until the oil is hot and then fry the chicken (medium fire) for about 3 minutes.
Turn and cook for another 2 minutes.
After the chicken is cooked, take it out of the pan and put it aside.

title: no bake pie
directions: Soften cream cheese in medium bowl.
Cream together with powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Gently fold in fruit cocktail and pour in pie crust.
Let stand until firm.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Brown ground beef and chopped onions; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning. Spread 2 cups meat mixture in greased pie plate.
Top with green chilies.
Beat until smooth the milk, eggs and Bisquick; pour over meat mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with desired toppings.
Makes one 8-inch pie or 6 servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place a layer of
pork	chops
in ovenproof dish.
(May brown pork chops, if
desired.) Salt and pepper chops.
Sprinkle uncooked rice on top of chops.
Pour chicken rice soup on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: brown sugar-baked onions
directions: Peel onions and scoop out small hole in top of each.
Place in glass baking dish.
Put 1 slightly rounded tablespoonful of brown sugar in the hollow of each onion.
(I use a small handful.)
Dot with margarine.
Microwave loosely covered with waxed paper, on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender, basting with pan juices twice.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Let stand for 3 minutes.
You can bake these in the oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: flossie cantrell's chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in heavy pan.
Stir until well blended. Add egg yolks and milk.
Place over low heat and cook until very thick.
Add butter and vanilla and put in cooked pie shell.
Beat egg whites stiff, adding 6 tablespoons sugar gradually.
Put on pie and brown.

title: glorified peas
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Mix with other ingredients, other than potato chips.
Put in casserole and top with potato chips, crushed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pan american beans
directions: Brown beef gradually over high heat; add other ingredients. Mix well and bake at 325° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour and spices.
Add alternately with buttermilk. Blend well after each addition.
Pour into pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground chuck and diced onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Drain and pour spaghetti sauce into beef, just 3/4 of jar. Boil lasagne noodles until tender; drain.
Prepare 9 x 13-inch dish by pouring sauce on bottom, just enough so noodles won't stick.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix cornstarch and 1 cup sugar in 2-quart saucepan.
Beat egg yolks well.
Add egg yolks and milk to sugar mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in vanilla.
Add butter.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Mix together the lemon juice, lemon rind, sugar and egg yolks; cook in double boiler until mixture begins to thicken.
Add egg whites; cook about 1 minute.
Cool.
Before serving, garnish with whipped cream; top with a cherry.
Serves 4.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Line a pastry lined 9-inch pie plate with a double thickness of foil.
Bake in a 450° oven for 8 minutes.
Remove foil. Bake for 4 to 5 minutes more until golden.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: fresh tomato and cucumber marinade
directions: Cut
the tomatoes into wedges.	Peel and cut the cucumber into 1-inch chunks.
Combine the remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour this mixture over the vegetables and refrigerate.
Stir several times to coat.
Let stand for several hours to allow the flavor to blend.

title: jewelled mini cheese cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix crumbs, butter and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon of mixture into ungreased muffin cups.
Press in firmly.
Beat cheese and sugar together until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Fill crumb-lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: black night sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
Great on steaks, ribs or chicken.

title: swedish meat balls for slow cooker
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine ground meats, bread crumbs, 1 cup of the half and half, eggs, onion and seasonings.
Form 1-inch meat balls.

title: allegro's stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix water, bulgur, onion, salt and garlic powder in 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes or until boiling; stir.
Cover and let stand until water is absorbed, about 10 minutes.
Cut thin slice from stem end of each bell pepper.
Remove seeds and membranes; rinse.
Arrange peppers, cut ends up, in circle in pie plate (9 x 1 1/4 or 10 x 1 1/2 inches). Crumble ground beef into bulgur mixture; stir in 1 cup of the tomato sauce.
Fill each pepper with about 1/2 cup mixture.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over peppers.

Cover tightly and microwave on High 12 to 14 minutes, rotating pie plate 1/2 turn after 7 minutes, until beef mixture is done (160° on meat thermometer). Sprinkle peppers with cheese; let stand, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: rice dish
directions: Brown rice and mushrooms in butter; add soups.
Place in oven for an hour at 375°.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt
chocolate
in
cup
of boiling water.
Cool. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla and chocolate; mix until blended.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Add sifted dry ingredients
alternately
with
buttermilk
to
chocolate mixture, beating
after each addition until batter is smooth. Fold in stiffly
beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into 3 (8 or 9-inch) layer pans, bottom lined with wax paper.
Bake in 350° oven
for 30
to
40 minutes. Cool.
Frost with Coconut-Pecan Frosting.

title: forget-me-not cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 3/4 cup sugar, add 1/4 cup at a time.
Add vanilla and fold in chips. Drop by teaspoon on foil-covered cookie sheets.

title: cup salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O and marshmallows in the boiling water. Add the remaining ingredients.
Makes 2 good size molds.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Knead all together with hands.
Add up to 3 tablespoons of water, as required.
Shape into walnut-sized balls.
Cook in 375° oven 15 minutes or until crisp outside.

title: bacon-cheddar dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Transfer dip to a tray and serve with assorted vegetables or crackers.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: chicken tater tot hot dish
directions: Place chicken in buttered 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Stir together soups and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Spread frozen peas over top of soup.
Lay slices of cheese to cover the peas.
Top with a layer of Tater Tots.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour until bubbly and Tots are golden brown.

title: taco mix
directions: Add mix to one pound of hamburger while browning.

title: hot nacho dip
directions: Layer ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan as listed.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with nachos.

title: mom's homemade salad dressing
directions: Cook ingredients slowly in saucepan, stirring constantly so it doesn't curdle.
When thickened, remove from heat.
Add mustard as preferred (don't need much).
Little mayonnaise to give more zip. Add celery seed, if preferred.
This makes a small batch; can increase ingredients accordingly for larger amounts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple, pepper and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Shape in ball.
Cover in nuts and chill.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Line dish with vanilla wafers.
Slice bananas and put over crackers. Drain pineapple and put over bananas. Spread Eagle Brand over pineapple. Spread Cool Whip over Eagle Brand.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Put in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours. Slice and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together one at a time; add oil and mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt and spices sifted together and mix. Add carrots last.
Bake in three layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and ice cake.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine 1/2 cup catsup, hamburger, eggs, chopped onion, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper to taste in a 3-quart baking dish. Combine 1/2 cup catsup, vinegar, water, brown sugar and mustard. Punch hole in meat loaf and pour sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: boiled bacon dressing(for dandelion green or dutch lettuce)
directions: Cook bacon in frypan.
Remove bacon and crumble.
Add sugar, salt and flour to bacon drippings.
Beat egg and add vinegar and water and set aside.
When ingredients in frypan are thick and sauce-like, add the remaining mixture.
Continue to cook and stir.

title: whole lot of stuff cake
directions: Drain pineapple, saving the juice.
Bake cake according to directions substituting water with the pineapple juice.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef and bacon roll-ups
directions: Wrap a slice of bacon around each sausage and secure with a toothpick.
Layer the wrapped franks and brown sugar half at a time in a slow cooker.
Cook on low for 3 to 4 hours stirring occasionally.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes or longer.

title: tahitian supper
directions: Mix brown sugar and cornstarch and add the syrup drained from pineapple cubes; add the 1 cup water and 2 tablespoons vinegar. Cook, stirring constantly, until clear and thick.
Stir in cubed meat, pineapple cubes and the pepper strips.
Cook over low heat until heated through.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add sour cream and beat. Sift flour, baking soda and salt. Add to first mixture. Beat. Add vanilla and butter flavoring and mix. Flour and grease a large tube pan. Add cake to pan and bake at 275° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Blend dry ingredients.
Mash bananas and add to mix.	Stir in nuts.
Pour in greased floured loaf pan (1 large or 2 small pans).
Bake at 350° until done.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut stew meat into small pieces and flour.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter or margarine.
Remove from pan and brown the floured meat.
Add the bouillon, mushrooms, onions, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Add sour cream and simmer 30 more minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Squeeze out the water, well.
Mix all ingredients.

title: apple punch
directions: Combine both juices and punch into one container with orange slices and chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: beans and pasta
directions: In olive oil, saute garlic.
Add broth, tomato paste and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Add rosemary
and beans.
Smash a few beans and stir.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over pasta.

title: cola surprise chicken
directions: Place chicken in a covered casserole.
Pour catsup and Coke over it.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Pork chops, round steak or venison are good this way.

title: microwave meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Form into 18 meatballs.
Arrange in an 8 x 12-inch dish.
Cover with wax paper.

title: zesty carrot strips
directions: Cook carrots until tender, as desired.
Drain and place in even layer in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients and spread over carrots.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Good with green beans also.

title: microwave rice
directions: Pour 1 cup raw rice into cooker.
Add 2 cups water.
Secure lid.
Microwave
4 minutes on high, 12 minutes on low.
Let stand for 10 minutes (steam cooks rice). Fluff with a moist fork. Season to taste.
Yield 3 cups rice or 4 to 6 servings.
Cooking time can vary depending on wattage.

title: swiss potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft in a large kettle.
Stir in potatoes, salt, mustard, pepper and water.
Heat to boiling. Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until potatoes are soft.
Pour soup, a little at a time, into blender or food processor.
Process until smooth.
Return to kettle.
Stir in milk; heat slowly until it boils.
Stir in cheese.
Pour in bowls; sprinkle with parsley.

title: rhubarb brown betty
directions: Sift flour with soda and baking powder.
Pour over rhubarb and bake at 375° until done.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan on low heat for 30 minutes and let simmer.
Cut up chipped ham.
Add chipped ham to sauce. Amount of ham added is up to individual taste.
Continue to simmer until ham is heated through.
Serve on toasted bun with pickle relish.

title: best baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover last 10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool in pan before removing.

title: amigo
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder until red disappears from meat. Add tomato sauce and simmer until ready to serve. Add grated cheese and stir slightly. Serve over Fritos with tossed salad and buttered French bread.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour mixture into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until firm.

title: hot beef dip or spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and milk.
Then add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with chopped nuts, if desired.
Use with crackers.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Place potatoes in melted oleo. Sprinkle with minced onions and add salt and pepper to taste. Place in oven at 425° in covered dish until tender, about 30 minutes.
Remove lid and return to oven until brown.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Bring mixture (all but the Certo) to a boil. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and add Certo.
Stir until thick.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: chicken french-style
directions: Slice chicken breast.
Put into flour, then egg.
Heat oil and fry chicken.
Drain oil.
Put lemon, margarine, wine, parsley, pepper and salt in frying pan.
Add mushrooms and simmer 10 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: You will need a 13 x 8 x 2-inch rectangle pan (I prefer glass).

title: gourmet banana pudding
directions: Prepare instant pudding as directed on package, omitting 1/2 cup milk.
Stir in Cool Whip and sour cream until blended.
Cut bananas into thin slices and stir in pudding mixture.
Line bowl with vanilla wafers and pour banana pudding on top.
Cover with vanilla wafers.

title: quick quiche
directions: Lightly grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle shredded cheese and ham on bottom of plate.
In food processor or blender, place biscuit mix, eggs, butter, milk, Parmesan cheese, onion, mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix 30 seconds.
Pour mixture over ham and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Any meat can be used in recipe.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato paste.
Bring to a boil. Cook 2 hours.
Add tomato paste; cook 15 minutes, then serve or can.

title: pear mincemeat
directions: Grind pears, apple, orange and lemon together.
Add other ingredients.
Cook slowly about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Pack in clean hot jars and seal while still hot.

title: boy choir cookies
directions: Bake approximately 12 minutes at 350°.

title: jalapeno cheese bread
directions: Let the dough thaw until pliable.
(To thaw dough in the microwave, remove frozen loaf from plastic tray and wrap in wax paper.
Microwave on Low power for 6 minutes.
Let dough rest for 15 minutes.)

title: tex-mex meat loaf for two
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons chopped chiles and next 6 ingredients; stir well.
Add ground beef and stir just until blended.
Shape mixture into 2 (4 x 2-inch) loaves.
Place in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix graham cracker crumbs with butter or margarine, chopped walnuts and cinnamon.
Press into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Combine sugar, salt, cream cheese, vanilla, almond extract and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Blend in dairy sour cream.
Pour into prepared crust. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.
Chill for 4 to 5 hours before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: puppy chow for people
directions: Melt the chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter.
Stir in the vanilla.
Pour mixture over the Chex cereal; coat it real well.
Add the powdered sugar; shake it up in a large bag or sealed container.

title: lo-cal fruit salad
directions: Put all fruit in a large mixing bowl.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar-free Tang and mix well but gently.
Then add 1 small box sugar-free vanilla or lemon instant pudding.
Again, mix well but gently.
Chill before serving.
Flavor improves overnight.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans and sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon sugar, shaking pan to coat all sides.
In a large mixing bowl, cream together eggs, oil, remaining 2 cups sugar and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.

title: peanut butter quickies
directions: Pour syrup and sugar in a pot and bring to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter and turn the burner off.
Remove the pot from the burner.
Stir in corn flakes until all are coated.
Immediately spread mixture into a cookie sheet.
After mixture has cooled, cut into squares and serve.

title: golden anniversary punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to boiling point and boil for 3 minutes. Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and freeze in three 1/2 gallon cartons.
Take out 1 hour ahead of serving time and thaw to a slush.
When ready to serve, mix one quart ginger ale to a 1/2 gallon carton.
Serves 50 people.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Heat soup.
Dissolve Knox and water in hot soup.
Cool slightly.
Combine with other ingredients.
Put in loaf pan or mold.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with crisp crackers.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Brown bacon until crumbly; lay aside.
Cook onion with mustard, vinegar and brown sugar in a little of the bacon fat for 20 minutes, covered.
Put sauce and bacon over beans and bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: coated pecans
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add brown sugar and vanilla. Pour pecans into mixture and stir real good.
Take out and put on greased cookie sheet.
Do not touch on cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 250°.
Turn off oven and
leave in for 30 minutes. Store in airtight container.

title: apricot-glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook and cut up potatoes.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish and set aside.
In a saucepan, combine all ingredients, except the butter and pecans.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes, then add butter and pecans.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts and set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans and bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk and water on low heat. Mix in cherries, pineapple and nuts. Mix well. Put into tube pan. Let set for 7 to 10 days before cutting.

title: waffles
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Separate eggs.
Add milk to egg yolks and dry ingredients.
Add melted butter.
Beat egg whites well.
Add.

title: one dish breakfast
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Whip eggs.
Add all ingredients. Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut in squares.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate squares.
Add sugar and flour. Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into ungreased pie pan.
Bake at 300° about 30 minutes or until done.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Cut up bacon into short lengths and fry along with the hamburger and diced onions.
Stir often to break up ground beef chunks.
Drain off fat.
Briefly boil or steam potatoes, celery and carrots until crisp-tender.
Put meat-onion mixture into a roaster or large deep casserole.
Gently fold in the cooked, drained vegetables, mushroom soup and tomato juice.
Stir well.
Fold in cooked, drained spaghetti and frozen peas.
Lay slices of cheese on top before baking for 1 hour at 350°.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: caramel nut brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk and stir frequently.
Combine cake mix with melted butter and remaining milk.
Spread 2/3 cake mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chips and nuts, then drizzle caramel sauce over that.
Top with remaining cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool before slicing.

title: pink stuff
directions: Combine ingredients and put in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.
Kids love it, but don't tell them what's in it.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix together the apples, oil, sugar, eggs, walnuts and vanilla.
Combine rest of dry ingredients with apple mixture; stir until well moistened.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Mix soup, pepper, celery, rice and water.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased casserole dish, then add sausage.
Cover with foil and cook for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and cook for 15 more minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Hand mix.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell, uncooked.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan or 12-cup Bundt pan. Sprinkle pecans over bottom of pan.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon. Put one half of mixture in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with uncooked rhubarb.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in electric fry pan on low.
Simmer about 20 minutes.

title: orange chip cookies
directions: In medium bowl, cream oleo, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla. Beat egg yolk until well blended.
Gradually stir in flour until smooth.
Stir in orange rind, chocolate chips and walnuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until bottom of cookies are golden brown.
Tops will be white.
Bake about 10 minutes.

title: hash brown sausage bake
directions: In a bowl, combine sour cream and soup.
Stir in hash brown potatoes, sausage, cheese and onion.
Put mixture into a greased 3-quart baking dish.
Toss together cornflake crumbs and melted margarine.
Sprinkle mixture over top.

title: breakfast before brunch casserole
directions: Spray or grease a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Trim crust off bread.
Break trimmed bread coarsely and line dish with it. Brown sausage and drain.
Layer sausage on top of bread.
Layer cheese on top of sausage.
Beat eggs with a fork.
Mix eggs with milk, mustard and dash of Tabasco.
Pour over top of casserole. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, next morning at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: new england dinner
directions: Cover meat with cold water.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add vegetables and continue to simmer 1 hour more.
Drain and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: old fashioned corn bread
directions: Stir and pour in a well-greased skillet. Bake for 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven!
Cream butter, margarine, cream cheese and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour and then vanilla, mixing well.
Pour in a greased and floured tube pan.
Put cake in cold oven, then turn oven to 300° for 1 1/2 hour baking time.

title: shrimp and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to the package directions.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter and drain.
Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit
and add enough water to make 3 cups.
Cook until thickened.	Cool.
Fold in fruit, leaving bananas until last. Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak beans and 1 tablespoon salt in 2 1/2 cups water in an 8-quart pan overnight.
Cook beans next day for about 2 hours. Cover with cold water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and pepper and dried onions.
Put in pan.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours.
Mix ketchup, Karo, brown sugar and mustard.
Pour this over beans when baking. Put pork chops and strips of bacon on top.
If you want you can use hot sauce with mixture.

title: beef stroganoff(microwave)
directions: Combine butter, onion and garlic in 1-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on full power for 2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until onion is tender.
Trim excess fat from meat.
Cut meat into thin, bite-size strips.
Add meat to casserole.
Cook, covered, on full power for 3 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Continue cooking on Cook Level 3 for 10 to 13 minutes or until meat is cooked.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In small saucepan over low heat, dissolve 2 tablespoons bouillon in water.
In large bowl combine beef, crumbs, onions, bouillon, liquid and egg.
Mix well and shape into 18 meatballs. In skillet brown meatballs and pour off fat.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly oil an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. In large bowl, stir zucchini, oil and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients and combine well.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 30 minutes and cut into squares to serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring continually.
When it forms a hard ball in cold water, remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until cool.
Add nuts and spread onto cake.

title: squash delight
directions: Combine all ingredients except the cracker crumbs.
Place in a buttered 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes until firm.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening and cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Sift all dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Sit in refrigerator and chill.
Roll in balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: good stuff
directions: Brown pork with onion. Cook rice according to package instructions. Combine pork, rice, soup, water and sauerkraut (including liquid). Heat in casserole dish (covered) for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange cooked broccoli in a greased casserole.
Place chicken over broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese and then crumbs over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: watergate salad
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Add pineapple and stir until creamy.
Add whipped topping, nuts, coconut and marshmallows. Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Serve chilled.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Mix together; save 3/4 cup and mix with 1/4 cup milk for topping.
Use Aztec tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes with topping and cheese on top of enchilada.
After cooking, top with salsa sauce.
Serve with a salad.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix; press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: summer squash medley
directions: To leftover mashed potatoes, add beaten egg white only.
Form into balls. Drop into hot fat.

title: strawberry pies
directions: Cook crust and cool.
Cap berries and slice them.
Chill for 1 hour.
Boil together water, sugar and cornstarch.
Take from heat and add strawberry jello.
Mix thoroughly.
Place saucepan in refrigerator to chill until it begins to thicken.
Place berries in pie shell and drizzle jello mixture over berries, making sure to completely cover them all.
Let stand in refrigerator.
Just before serving, put Cool Whip over top.
Serves 8.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all together; roll out.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cut into narrow strips.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes.

title: passion fruit party dessert
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
In a saucepan, combine egg yolks, juice and 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens, about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat, add softened gelatin and stir until gelatin is dissolved; cool.
Oil a 10-inch tube pan.
Tear angel food cake into small 1-inch pieces.
Put a layer of pieces of prepared pan.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in the remaining 3/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold cooked mixture into beaten whites.
Pour part of mixture over cake layer and continue alternating layers until all cake pieces and cooked mixture are used.
Chill 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Unmold and frost with whipped cream.
Makes 16 servings.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix well and pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Drain fat.
Add beer.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste; simmer 15 minutes.
Add all seasoning, stirring well after each one.
Add jalapenos, whole.
Cook on low for about 4 hours.
Remove jalapenos.
Cook 2 more hours or slow cook overnight in crock-pot.

title: atlanta pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops both sides in electric skillet, take out, then saute onion and celery in butter.
Take out, then brown rice.
Then add to rice, tomato sauce, brown sugar and sauteed seasonings. Simmer for 5 minutes, then add pork chops on top.
Lay bay leaves on top.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes at low temperature on simmer.
You can add water if needed.
Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Bone chicken.
Add all ingredients together and pour into a large casserole dish or 2 medium ones.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: potatoes and spam
directions: Place potatoes, onion and Spam, alternating, in casserole. Blend soup and milk; pour over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Boil chicken for 1/2 hour.
Add vegetables and seasonings to chicken.
Boil for 15 minutes, then simmer until vegetables are tender, about 5 minutes.
Serves 1.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Shape into a loaf and place in shallow glass baking dish (11 x 9-inch).
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Serve with beef gravy, green beans and mashed potatoes.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Brown ground beef well.
While browning, add onion, garlic, oregano, thyme, salt and pepper.
When beef is done, drain well. Add cheese and beaten eggs.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Mixture will be very stiff and dry.

title: tangy zucchini spears
directions: Combine vinegar, honey, celery seed, mustard seed, turmeric and dry mustard.
Boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over zucchini.
Cover and chill.
Drain before serving.
Serves 8.

title: white chili
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic in oil until tender. Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mints
directions: Combine ingredients well.
Roll into balls and shape with sugar coated molds.
Makes 20 to 30 mints.

title: pineapple strawberry shortcake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed in step 2 on package except add 1/2 cup of the topping mix to dry mix; reserve remaining topping mix.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: potato soup
directions: Put vegetables, spices and broth together in Dutch oven.
Cook 15 minutes on medium-low until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and bring to a slow boil.
Add flour to sour cream and mix well.
Take 1 cup of hot soup and add slowly to sour cream.
Then put back in soup and cook until soup thickens.

title: country soup
directions: Put large kettle on stove.
Add carrots, white beans, green beans, bay leaf, onion, oregano, beef and tomato sauce.
Simmer and stir often, until beef is mixed throughout with vegetables. Add water to top of vegetables; let simmer for about 40 minutes. Add cabbage, tomatoes and potatoes; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add noodles and peas; cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: pico de gallo(salsa with cilantro)
directions: Dice tomatoes by hand. Put onion and jalapeno in food processor (I use a little chopper) and chop very fine. Chop cilantro in food processor fine. Mix all ingredients together. Keep refrigerated until use.

title: jello mold
directions: Prepare Jell-O with one cup hot water.
Chill in refrigerator until slightly firm.
Mix pineapple, crushed nuts and coconut together.
Mix softened cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Beat Milnot until frothy; blend in cream cheese, pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Whip slightly firm Jell-O and add to whipped Milnot.
Pour into Jell-O mold.
Set until firm.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup hot water.
Add cake mix, oil, eggs and 1/2 box of strawberries.
Pour into 2 (8 or 9-inch) layer pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: custard peach pie(bryce's style)
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
Toss with lemon juice.
In a saucepan scald 1 cup milk.
To scalded milk add 1 cup sugar and whisk until mixed over medium heat.
When heated through, add 1/3 of the hot milk mixture to 2 tablespoons cornstarch, whisking to mix thoroughly.
Add a dash of salt and 1/2 cup cold milk and whisk until mixed.
Add this mixture back into saucepan milk mixture and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add 2 tablespoons butter, vanilla, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour into baked shell.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with topping.

title: mava hudgins' corn pudding
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Add butter to top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute onions and green peppers in hot oil until yellow.
Add ground beef and fry until mixture falls apart. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour, removing cover last 15 minutes. Serve hot.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: chicken-egg-lemon soup(from greece:  soupa avgolemono)
directions: Boil the water.
Add chicken, onion, celery, carrot, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Strain the broth.
Remove bones and the skin.
Chop the meat and the vegetables.
Add to the boiling broth and the rice.
Cover and cook 20 minutes or until tender.
Salt to taste.

title: brazillian beef
directions: Mix all together in casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: red wonder cake
directions: Grease and flour or line with wax paper 2 (8-inch) cake pans. Make a paste of red cake coloring and cocoa.
Cream the Crisco and granulated sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla and the red paste and mix well.
Sift flour and salt.
Add to mixture alternately with buttermilk. Dissolve baking soda in vinegar.
Fold at once into batter.
Do not beat.
Pour into baking pans and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes, or until done.
Spread icing on cooled cake.
Can also be made into cupcakes.

title: layered mexican casserole
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Brown hamburger in skillet; add taco powder and 1/2 cup of water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In large saucepan bring
soups and tomatoes to full boil.
Remove from heat;
add hamburger
meat.
In
large
casserole line bottom with
tortilla shells
making
sure
all
bottom
is covered, overlapping	if necessary.	Spoon
half
of
the mixture from saucepan
on	top, smooth
and
add
layer of shells and then remainder
of meat sauce.
Top with cheese and bake 1 1/2 hour or until cheese browns.

title: treasure chicken divan
directions: Cook rice and broccoli as directed on package.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer rice, then chicken, then broccoli.
In another dish, mix water chestnuts, mushroom soup and mayonnaise. Spread over layered ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
If desired, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash
cucumbers
and
fill
jars, add 1 head of dill, 1 slice of
onion
and
clove
of garlic if desired can be added. Mix
and bring to boil the vinegar and salt.
Pour hot liquid over cucumbers and seal.

title: poor man's salisbury steak
directions: Mix all except soup together.
Form into patties and brown in skillet.
Drain excess grease.
Add cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 can of water.
Simmer over low heat for 30 minutes, turning patties occasionally.
Extra gravy can be served over potatoes or rice.

title: sylvia's russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
To make tea, blend 1 or 2 tablespoons to 1 cup hot water, depending on strength desired.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Put in unbaked pie shell.
Mix well and bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° until done.
Can put meringue on top or Cool Whip.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken; cook bacon until crisp.
Add onion and pepper; cook until tender.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Mix spaghetti, chicken, onion and pepper mixture with remaining ingredients.
Put into very hot oven, about 450°, and let heat until entire mixture is bubbly.
More sour or chicken broth may be added if mixture is too dry.

title: strawberry jello delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add strawberries.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Spread on top of second layer.
Chill 24 hours.

title: "purple cow" shakes
directions: Pour juice concentrate and milk into blender.
Add ice cream. Cover and blend on high speed for 30 seconds.
Serve right away, 3 or 4 shakes.

title: old-fashioned bread stuffing
directions: Melt butter; cook onion, celery, celery leaves and parsley until tender.
Mix with bread crumbs.
Add broth a little at a time until well moistened.
Bake (covered) in a buttered casserole for 30 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Uncover and cook an additional 15 minutes to crisp the top.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in double boiler over low heat.
After melted, put 1/2 of mixture into a greased bun pan larger than 9 x 13-inch.
Cool this in refrigerator until hard.
Save the other 1/2 in double boiler for later (no heat now).
Mix together dry regular vanilla pudding, evaporated milk and margarine.
Boil 1 minute.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix and add vanilla or maple flavoring; stir until blended.
Spread this over 1st layer.
Mix Spanish peanuts in
the mixture in double boiler and spread on top of 2nd layer.
Store in refrigerator until used.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles in boiling water for 20 minutes.
Drain, rinse and set aside.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients into medium bowl.
Whisk together pumpkin, oil, honey, milk and egg in large bowl.
Stir in dry ingredients and nuts.
Spoon into muffin pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quicky fruitcake
directions: In large bowl, combine walnuts, raisins, dates and candied fruit.
Coat well with 1/4 cup flour.
In large mixer bowl, combine 3/4 cup flour and remaining ingredients.
Blend well with mixer.
Stir in the fruit and nut mixture, mixing thoroughly. Spread in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Brush, while warm, with Orange Glaze.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: quiche
directions: Brush pie shell with small amount of the beaten eggs.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
If using metal pan, bake shell in preheated 450° oven until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
If using glass pie plate, bake shell at 425°.
Cool on wire rack.
Reduce oven temperature to 375° for metal pan or 350° for pie plate.
Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven until knife inserted halfway between center and outside edge comes out clean, 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aspirin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour pan.
Remove toys from countertop.
Measure 2 cups flour; get baking powder.
Remove kids hands from flour.
Put flour, baking powder and salt into sifter. Vacuum mixture the kids spilled onto floor.
Get eggs; answer phone.
Separate eggs.
Warm baby's bottle.
Help daughter figure math problem.
Answer door bell.
Take 1/2-inch salt from greased pan.
Look for kids.
Put mess in trash can and dishes into dishwasher.
Put cake on grocery list.
Take an aspirin!

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients; add milk. Mix and pour over oleo.
Do not stir.
Place fruits and syrup on top.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 40 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and Ricotta, sugar and eggs.
Add sour cream, flour and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Place in large spring pan that has been buttered and sprinkled with graham cracker crumbs on bottom and sides.
Place in pan containing water to cover half of baking pan.
Bake at 350°
for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn oven off and do not open for 4 hours.

title: pumpkin bread or bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into 3 greased bread pans and bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Or, pour into large greased cake pan and bake for 45 minutes at 350° (or until done).
Cut into bars.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add flour and cook 2 minutes.
Let cool.
Cook potatoes.
Set aside.
Bring clam juice to boil.
Add hot clam juice to flour mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Add clams, potatoes and half and half. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
You can also add shrimp and scallops to recipe.

title: baked peaches
directions: Place drained peaches in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, holes up. Mix brown sugar and flour.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Sprinkle generously with cinnamon.
Place small piece of butter in each peach center.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle pecans over each peach.
Bake an additional 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute celery and green pepper; add soup, mushrooms, pimento, salt and pepper.
Add a little milk to thin; layer in 9 x 13-inch pan:
chicken, spaghetti, sauce and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: reeses balls
directions: Mix well butter and peanut butter.
Add confectioners sugar slowly.
Mix with mixer until stiff.
Finish with hands.
Mix like pie dough.
Shape into balls.
Lay on waxed paper.
Stick with toothpicks.
Chill well, overnight in refrigerator.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle milk until blended. Add strawberries, pineapple and nuts. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Freeze. Cut into squares.

title: baked ham slice
directions: Cut slashes in edge of ham slice.
Sprinkle or dot with mustard and brown sugar.
Place in heavy skillet or baking pan. Pour on milk at side of ham slice until it barely reaches top of ham.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: cheddar cabbage wedges
directions: Cut cabbage into 8 wedges, leaving a portion of the core. Steam wedges in boiling salted water for 10 to 15 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain; remove core.
Place wedges in a greased 3-quart dish.
In medium saucepan, saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper and cook until bubbly.
Gradually add milk; cook and stir until thickened. Pour over cabbage.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Brown garlic and onion in a small amount of oil.
Pour tomatoes (including juice) into blender and chop.
Add to garlic and onions.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and parsley.
Bring to a boil and cook rapidly for 5 minutes (to melt sugar).
Lower flame and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in oregano last few minutes.

title: mrs. smith's pineapple dessert
directions: Bake white cake mix as directed in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan. Cool.
Mix vanilla instant pudding as directed.
Blend in cream cheese with mixer.
Chill and then pour over cake, spreading evenly.
Place drained crushed pineapple on top.
Mix Dream Whip (which is fat-free) and cover cake with it.
Refrigerate.
Can be made ahead of time, even the day before.

title: date balls
directions: Cook dates, butter and sugar 8 minutes at slow bubble.
Take off stove and drop in Rice Krispies plus 1 teaspoon vanilla extract.
Pour on greased platter.
Shape into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in nuts, fruit and buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture. Chill overnight or at least 1 hour.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart on a lightly greased baking sheet and place a pecan half on each cookie.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 6 dozen or more.

title: chocolate sugar drops
directions: Cream butter, oil, powdered sugar, 1/2 cup granulated sugar and the egg in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt in small bowl.
Add to creamed mixture with vanilla, stirring until dough is smooth. Cover; refrigerate 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Shape dough into balls the size of marbles. Place 2 inches apart; flatten each cookie to about 1/3 inch thick with bottom of glass dipped into granulated sugar.
Bake 10 minutes or until firm.
Don't overbake.
Remove to wire racks to cool. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl mix all ingredients and chill.

title: double chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift into large bowl the sugar and plain flour.
Mix in pan and bring to boil the oleo, cocoa and water.
Pour boiled mixture over dry ingredients; stir well and add buttermilk, salt, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: clouds at sunrise
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg white until frothy.
Add cream of tartar, then gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in graham crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Spread whipped cream over top and spoon pie filling over cream.
Chill.

title: baked pancake
directions: Mix flour and milk in a bowl.
Add beaten eggs and nutmeg; beat lightly.
Melt butter in a large skillet, taking care not to burn.
Add egg mixture and bake.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Cover with orange marmalade and serve.

title: jan's strawberry punch
directions: Combine sugar and Kool-Aid with 1/2 gallon water.
Stir until both are dissolved.
Pour in thawed strawberries.
Mix Jell-O according to package directions and add to mixture.
Add enough water to make 1 gallon.
Put in plastic gallon jug and freeze. Shake frequently until slushy.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until they are tender; cool.
Combine soup, oil, vinegar, mustard, salt, pepper and sugar in a saucepan.
Cook until thoroughly heated, then cool completely.
Put vegetables in a bowl and pour soup mixture over all.
Stir to mix well. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix.
Bake in lightly greased muffin tins at 350° until done.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and boiling water; set aside to cool. Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Beat eggs; pour yeast and flour into sugar and shortening mixture.
Add eggs; mix well. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out dough; cut with pastry cutter. Dip in melted margarine; place in pan.
Place pan and rolls in a warm place; let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake in a 450° oven until brown.

title: pie crust anyone can make
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together with pastry blender, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well together and let rest 10 minutes before rolling out.
I find it best to refrigerate this 10 minutes.
You don't even need to use Crisco.
I have used a cheap brand.

title: chicken squares(makes 4 to 8 servings)
directions: Blend cream cheese with melted butter until smooth.
Add chicken breasts, salt and pepper to taste, milk and onions.
Mix well.

title: oatmeal mounds
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and heat to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add remaining 3 ingredients.
Mix together and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Cool, eat and enjoy.
Children love this.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Combine blueberries, 1 cup of sugar and 1/4 cup water in saucepan and simmer on low heat until berries soften.
In a separate bowl, mix cornstarch and 3 tablespoons water.
Add cornstarch to blueberry mixture.
Mix together flour, margarine and pecans.
Press evenly in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake crust at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Allow to cool.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Sift together flour, cornstarch and sugar.
Cream in butter and mix as you would for pie crust.
When well mixed, put in an ungreased square pan and pat in evenly.
Then pick the entire surface with a fork, as you would a pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Cut into squares and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Do not spare the sugar!

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Coat chicken with flour and fry.
Put in soup pot and cover with mixture of rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Take out and add 1 can water chestnuts and slices of green pepper.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Serve with rice.

title: raisin granola
directions: Combine oats, coconut, wheat germ, nuts and salt in large bowl. Stir in condensed milk, add oil and mix thoroughly.
Spray cookie sheet and spread mixture evenly.
Bake at 300°, stirring occasionally for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and stir in raisins. Cool.
Store in closed container.

title: saucy potatoes for company
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 15 to 20 minutes, until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add flour, stirring until well blended. Cook one minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir until cheese melts.
Stir in potatoes and pimento.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes six servings.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix the pecans, flour and butter.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat together the cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on first layer.
Mix the pudding, milk and lemon flavoring.
Spread on second layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, oleo and milk together.
Bring to a boil, stirring all the time.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: sugar-free dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with oleo and spread in 8 x 10 pan. Soften cream cheese and sweetener, then spread on crumbs.

title: mediterranean sandwiches
directions: Drizzle olive oil on bread.
Brush garlic on bread.
Sprinkle black pepper, oregano and basil to taste on bread.
Layer bell pepper, onion, tomato and Provolone cheese on bread.
Add layer of sliced black olives.
(May add any sliced meat of choice, if desired.)
Wrap in plastic wrap 1 to 4 hours before serving. Serves 4.

title: apple muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add oil, egg, and milk.
Stir just until blended.
Fold in apple.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 20-25 minutes.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat eggs into mixture.
Add pineapple, including the juice.
Remove the crust from the white bread and cut into bite size pieces.
Add to other ingredients. Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole (in water).

title: overnight french toast for guests
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with extra margarine. Cut bread into 1-inch thick slices.
Arrange in bottom of dish. In large bowl, mix all ingredients, except butter.
Pour over bread, cover with foil and refrigerate 8 to 36 hours.

title: giambotto(vegetable stew)
directions: In a large saucepan, saute in olive oil the onion and garlic. Add the tomatoes, potatoes, string beans, eggplant, salt and pepper. Allow to simmer for 1 hour.
Add the zucchini squash and allow to simmer for another 1/2 hour. Serve hot in soup bowls with buttered hot Italian bread.

title: crab-artichoke casserole
directions: Drain artichokes and cut each heart into fourths.
Arrange artichokes and eggs in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour and remove from heat. Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire; cook over low heat until thickened.
Fold in crab meat and pour over artichokes and eggs.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 30 minutes or until bubbly in 350° oven.

title: pork chops and white gravy
directions: Fry seasoned pork chops quickly in a large black-iron skillet that has been lined with a little cooking oil.
Remove chops to a heated plater and place in a warm oven.
Add 3/4 cup milk and stir, scraping off debris from the bottom of the skillet.
Bring to a boil and continue to stir for a minute.
Add sifted flour, a little at a time, and blend well.
If it gets too thick, add a little more milk.
Add pepper to taste and serve over mashed potatoes.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all together until dough is formed.
Drop into hot broth. Cook, covered, 10 to 12 minutes with lid on pan.
Do not remove cover until time is up.
Don't overmix dough; it will be lumpy.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix with fork and pour into unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until pie will not shake.

title: vegetable stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In large skillet, melt butter (margarine); add onion.
Cook over medium for 5 minutes.
Add carrots, spinach and basil.
Cook another 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 cup Ricotta cheese.
Stuff into shells.
Put in baking dish.
Cover with sauce and cheese.
Bake 15 minutes or until heated through.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Bring brown sugar, margarine and white syrup to a boil.
Cook five minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and baking soda. Pour over popcorn.
Mix well.
Put in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 250° for one hour.
Stir every ten minutes.

title: savory red cabbage
directions: In large kettle, saute onion in butter until soft.
Add cabbage; cook over low heat, stirring often, for 10 minutes.
Add the apples, wine, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper; mix well. Cover kettle; lower heat and simmer for 1 hour, stirring several times.
Uncover kettle; raise heat.
Cook until all liquid is absorbed.
Pour into large serving bowl.
Makes 8 servings.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain fruit. Fold all ingredients together. Refrigerate.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: chocolate wacky cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Make cake according to box instructions.
Boil pineapple with 1 cup sugar for 5 minutes.
Punch holes in top of cake and spread pineapple on top.
Make pudding and layer on top of pineapple. Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle pecans on top.

title: crockery cherry cobbler
directions: Pour pie filling into a 5-quart slow cooker. Spread evenly.

title: pistachio bars
directions: Place all the above ingredients in bowl and mix with hands. Add chocolate chips, if desired, or pat on top after patting into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Will look goopy but will set up.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Get a pan out, then get a bowl to mix it up.
Get flour, some butter and stir it up then.
Get 1 egg to put in and some peanut butter.
Then get one a half a cup of sugar, stir it all up then put some baking soda in it and bake until it is done!

title: dr. cookie's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Coat 2 baking sheets with nonstick cooking spray.
Beat margarine and sugars with a mixer until smooth.
Add eggs; beat again.
Add milk and vanilla; beat again until smooth.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; beat until well mixed.
Add chocolate chips and stir.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart. Flatten with back of a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until light brown.
Cool on wire rack.

title: juicy chicken meatballs
directions: Mix together hamburger (uncooked), water, salt and uncooked oatmeal.
Chill for 30 minutes.
After meat mixture is chilled, roll into balls.
Coat all sides of meatballs with flour.
Brown on all sides in a skillet with small amount of oil.
Add undiluted chicken soup to top of meatballs and simmer for 20 minutes, making sure balls don't stick to pan.
Keep soup scooped onto top of meatballs so they are seasoned well.

title: homemade doughnuts
directions: Mix together the sugar, eggs, oil, milk and salt.
Sift together 3 times the nutmeg, cinnamon, baking powder, 3 cups flour and ginger.
Gradually add dry sifted ingredients to liquid ingredients until blended, then add vanilla.
Add a little flour at a time to dough to make it easy to handle.
Roll out, cut and fry in shortening or oil at 340° in electric frying pan until brown.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Soak bread crumbs in water.
Cook onion in butter until light brown.
Mix meat, eggs, onion (season to taste with salt, pepper and a dash of nutmeg) and parsley.
Form into small balls.
Roll lightly in flour and brown in fat.
Remove meat balls to bowl. Make gravy from pan drippings and bouillon cubes.
Thicken with flour.
Return meat balls and cook for 20 minutes.

title: play clay
directions: Mix all ingredients; stir over low heat until thick and clings to a spoon (mixture should form a ball).
Remove saucepan to flat, dry surface to cool.
When cool, remove from pan and knead until smooth and pliable.
Store in airtight container.

title: congo bars
directions: Throw all ingredients in large bowl and stir after each one. If stiff, add a little milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt butter and stir into sugar.
Cool slightly and beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Then add nuts and chips. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Sift flour before measuring, then add baking powder and salt.
Sift twice more.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour. Add vanilla.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until done, at 325°.

title: debbie's barbecue sauce
directions: Chop onion and saute in oil until tender.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook on low heat until thickened.

title: santa fe-style chicken breasts
directions: Score each chicken breast half on both sides in a diamond pattern.
Rub chicken on both sides with mixture of chili powder and salt.
In skillet over medium-high heat, heat butter and oil. Add chicken breasts.
Cook about 3 minutes on each side or until browned and cooked throughout.
Remove chicken to plate.
To drippings in skillet, add marmalade and lime juice.
Heat over medium heat, stirring to loosen brown bits from skillet.
Return chicken to skillet; cook 2 to 3 minutes longer, until heated through and coated with glaze on both sides.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown and drain sausage; set aside.
In a medium saucepan, melt margarine over low heat.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Heat until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat; gradually add milk.
Cook rapidly, stirring constantly until sauce thickens.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Add sausage and serve over buttermilk biscuits.

title: goulash
directions: Okay. Wash them in a sink and then dry them off and then you have to put them in a pan and put them in there for 30 minutes, and then you take them out and then you eat them.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients on medium heat without stirring until the soft ball stage.
Add the remaining ingredients; stir until mixture stiffens, then pour onto waxed paper.
Separate quickly.
Let set and harden.

title: chocolate chess  pie
directions: Melt butter and cool.
Mix together sugar, cocoa, salt, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add butter; stir.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cake for birds
directions: This is not for human consumption, but for the birds.
They enjoy it during the winter months.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Stir flour, sugar, baking powder and salt until well mixed. Cut in peanut butter until mixture is coarse crumbs.
Stir in milk until well mixed.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on rack.
Serve warm.

title: delicious crispies
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, shortening and salt to scalded milk.
Cool.
Add 2 cups flour and beat well.
Add eggs, yeast and lemon flavoring.
Beat well and add remaining flour.
Knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until doubled (1 1/2 hours).

title: crock-pot beef roast
directions: Start on high; turn down to low.
Cook overnight.
Can be served with onions, potatoes, carrots and other vegetables as desired.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas and mix with other ingredients.
Serve.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix yogurt and honey.
Cut lime in half and squeeze juice from 1/2 of lime in mixture.
Remove pulp from entire lime and add. Mix.
Arrange fruit around bowl of dip.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: In 2-cup glass measure, add sugar and butter.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes until mixture boils, stirring every 30 seconds.
Combine in blender with dry milk.
Process until smooth. Refrigerate until needed.
Makes one cup.

title: fiesta corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 400° in 8 or 9-inch square baking pan or 10-inch ovenproof skillet.
Melt shortening in oven; tilt pan to coat bottom evenly.

title: nana's christmas cookies
directions: Place fruits in bowl.
Sift flour over fruit mixture.
In a separate glass bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar to egg whites and beat together.
Add fruit/flour mixture to egg white mixture.
Add nuts.
Fold well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown in color.
Check for doneness by flipping over.

title: ice cream goodie
directions: Melt sugar and butter.
Mix crackers, sugar and butter together.
Put in cake pan.
With flat end of spoon, pack crust firmly to bottom of pan.
Mix pudding, ice cream and milk until smooth.
Pour on crust.
Let set in refrigerator.
Spread Cool Whip over settled pudding.
Break up Heath bars and sprinkle over top.

title: lizzies
directions: Beat butter and eggs.
Add brown sugar.
In a bowl, measure flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add to butter and eggs gradually with liquid from raisins.
Add raisins and nuts.
Place by teaspoon on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Combine whipping cream, cocoa and sugar in a bowl.
Cover and chill.
Beat chilled mixture at medium speed of an electric mixer until stiff peaks form.
Set aside.

title: grandma kretchmer's blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add the egg.
Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Add blueberries.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes in 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring gently until combined.
Pour batter into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.

title: bird nests
directions: Melt white chocolate over low heat; stir frequently so chocolate doesn't scorch.
When completely melted stir in remaining ingredients.
Remove from heat.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let set until firm.

title: grandma swedish doughnuts
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, yolks, cream and milk with mixer until well blended. Add dry ingredients and mix with wooden spoon until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Chill dough one hour.
Roll out on floured board and cut with doughnut cutter. Fry in lard at 375°.
Dough may be put through doughnut maker in which case, do not chill.

title: cozze affogate con vino bianco
directions: Scrub and rinse tightly closed mussels thoroughly, until completely grit free.
Place in a large kettle with all ingredients.
Cover tightly.
Steam over low heat for 15 minutes or until shells open.
Jerk pot upwards from time to time to turn mussels.
Remove mussels and strain liquid.
Remove top shells from mussels and place on large platter.
Pour liquid over mussels. Enjoy!

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Cook and bone
chicken.
Reserve one cup of the chicken broth. Combine
soups,
green
chilies, spices, Tabasco sauce and chicken broth.
Blend
well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover the bottom of a 2
or
3 quart casserole with 2 cups corn chips. Spread half the chicken over this layer, then half the sauce, then half
the
grated
cheese.
Repeat,
ending
with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: avocado half-shells with seafood
directions: Combine chili sauce, mayonnaise, capers, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Toss chili mixture with seafood; chill.
Halve avocados lengthwise, twisting gently to separate halves.
Whack a sharp knife directly into seeds and twist to lift out.
Brush avocado with lemon juice; fill with seafood salad and garnish with lemon wedges.

title: puddingwiches
directions: Mix first three ingredients well with mixer.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Put pudding between cracker halves.
Freeze.

title: cranberry gelatin salad(12 servings)
directions: Heat cranberry sauce until melted.
Stir dry jello into sauce until dissolved.
Add drained pineapple and ginger ale.
Chill. Add celery and nuts, mixing well.
Chill again in mold.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Beat all together and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: rice a la malta(swedish recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients, folding together gently.
Chill completely.
Serves 6 to 8. May be served with raspberry or strawberry sauce.
Canned mandarin oranges is my favorite.

title: colorful vegetable saute
directions: In a Dutch oven, bring a small amount of water to boiling. Add onions; remove from heat.
Let stand for 1 minute.
Remove onions, reserving water.
When cool, tie each green onion around 4 or 5 raw asparagus spears.
Return water to boiling; add asparagus bundles.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 4 to 8 minutes or until crisp-tender.

title: raisin jumbo cookies
directions: Combine raisins and 1 cup of water in saucepan.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Cream shortening and sugar in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in raisins with liquid.
Add sifted dry ingredients gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by tablespoonfuls 1 inch apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Oven temperature for baking is 375°.

title: pineapple chiffon pie
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water about 5 minutes. Beat egg yolks slightly. Add 1/4 cup sugar, pineapple, lemon juice and salt. Cook on low heat until of custard consistency. Add the softened gelatin, stirring thoroughly. Cool. When mixture begins to thicken, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites to which has been added the other 1/4 cup of sugar.
Fill baked pie shell and chill.

title: congealed gazpacho salad with avocado cream
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1 cup tomato juice in a medium saucepan; let stand 1 minute.
Cook over low heat, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining tomato juice, white wine vinegar and next 4 ingredients.
Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in tomato and the next 3 ingredients. Spoon into 10 slightly oiled 1/2-cup molds.
Chill until firm. Unmold onto lettuce-lined salad plates.
Top with Avocado Cream. Garnish, if desired.
Yields 10 servings.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Prepare lasagna noodles according to directions.
Drain and lay flat on a large cutting board.
In a bowl, mix together the next 7 ingredients.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix everything together and pour into a greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 or 55 minutes.

title: zucchini and pasta
directions: Brown garlic in olive oil.
Peel.
Slice zucchini and brown. Add chopped onion and saute.
Brown lightly.
Add chicken broth. Add Wish-Bone Italian dressing.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook pasta separately.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: coconut pineapple cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add eggs one at a time to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk and flavorings, beating after each addition until smooth.
Add coconut and blend until smooth. Pour batter into three 9-inch layer pans lined on bottom with wax paper and greased and floured on sides.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, then turn out and cool on racks.
While cake layers are cooling, prepare Crushed Pineapple-Coconut Filling and Seven Minute Frosting.

title: okra and tomato casserole
directions: Cook okra until tender.
In saucepan, cook onion in 2 tablespoons margarine until tender (do not brown).
Blend flour and salt.
Add milk, all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened. Add cheese and stir until melted.
Fold in sliced okra and tomatoes.
Place into a one-quart casserole dish.
Combine bread crumbs with remaining margarine.
Sprinkle around edge of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mary's company cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Press in bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes and cool.
Turn oven down to 300°.
