Beat cream cheese in a large mixing bowl.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.
Add lemon peel and vanilla.
Beat in one egg at a time. Pour over crumb mixture.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend in mixer.
Makes one 9-inch pie.
Cook 10 minutes on 450° then 1 hour at 350°.

title: world's best sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter with powdered and granulated sugar.
Beat in eggs until smooth.
Slowly stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill dough for easy handling.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Dip in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 3 inches apart. Flatten each cookie with the bottom of a glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: basic roll dough
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt; cool.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour; beat well.
Beat in yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour to form soft dough, beating well.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise to double bulk.
(Except Refrigerator Rolls, do not let rise.)
Turn out on floured board and shape as desired.
Cover to rise.
Bake in greased pan at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: In a large saucepan cook potatoes, covered in boiling salted water for 25-30 minutes or until done.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Peel and cube potatoes.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix together milk and cherry juice.
Measure sifted flour and add to first mixture alternately with cherry-milk mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir in half of the cherries. Reserve the rest of cherries for icing.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: russian tea
directions: Use desired amount of cold water (hot, if you're in a hurry!) from faucet in sink.
Place in pan or tea kettle and turn on high heat.
Watch carefully so it does not burn.
When it bubbles, remove from heat; it is done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together dry ingredients and set aside.
Peel and slice apples.
Fill an 8x10 casserole dish with apples.
Mix butter in with dry ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 25 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 1/3 cup of juice.
Slice chicken in strips.
Stir-fry with garlic and ginger in oil.
Add pineapple, carrots, onions and pepper.
Steam for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti.

title: country pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup canned tomato sauce, bread crumbs, ground meat, onion, green pepper and oregano in a bowl; mix with a fork. Pat gently into sides and bottom of a greased 9-inch pie plate. Combine the Minute rice, 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce, 1 cup water, 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Spoon rice mixture into meat shell.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover; top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken dinner in foil
directions: Divide in half.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 servings.
Weight Watchers program count as:
1 bread, 4 vegetables and 4 ounces protein.

title: cheddar-dill popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Generously grease six 6-ounce custard cups or 8 medium muffin cups (2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch).
Beat eggs slightly in a medium bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients with fork or wire whisk just until smooth (do not overbeat).
Fill custard cups half full, muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: soft drink dairy slush
directions: Mix equal parts of Dr. Pepper (or other soft drink) and milk. Pour mixture into an 8 or 9-ounce cup.
Freeze for 1 hour.
Serve with a spoon.

title: cornbread dressing with shrimp
directions: Saut veggies in butter; add shrimp and cook until pink. Add soups and continue cooking until shrimp are done. Add crumbled cornbread; put mixture in casserole dish and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain well.
Stir in tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with sour cream and sprinkle with cheese.
Unroll crescent rolls and place on top of cheese. Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Crust will be golden brown.

title: chicken parmesan(quick, for the working woman)
directions: Wash chicken.
Dip in egg and then in bread crumb mix.
Heat oil in skillet.
Fry chicken until done.
Remove and lay chicken in baking pan.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese. Spread spaghetti sauce over chicken.
Add Mozzarella cheese and bake until cheese melts.
Serve over bed of buttered noodles. Serves 4.

title: potato cake(recipe over 100 years old)
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs; beat well after each addition.
Add cooled potatoes and chocolate.
Sift together flour, baking powder and spices.
Add to cake mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add black walnuts; this helps to make the cake.
Pour into two 9-inch lightly greased and floured pans and bake at 325° to 350° according to your stove. Let cool and frost with Potato Cake Icing.

title: potato-corn bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook bacon crisp.
Drain, reserving 1 tablespoon of drippings.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook over medium heat until tender.
Stir in corn, milk, margarine, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is hot and bubbly. Remove from heat.
Stir in potato flakes and sour cream until well blended.
Spoon mixture into greased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Top with bacon, Parmesan cheese and green onion.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: miniature cornmeal muffins
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine next 3 ingredients; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Place miniature paper baking cups into miniature (1 3/4-inch) muffin pan.
Coat inside of paper cups with cooking spray.
Spoon batter into cups, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes or until lightly browned. Yield:
4 dozen.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add vanilla and flour with baking powder and salt.
Then add milk and Crisco which have been brought to a boil.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Cover with the following
topping and slip under broiler until bubbly.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower (broken up) until tender; drain.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Pour over cauliflower in a 2-quart baking dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: 6-layer dinner
directions: Place ingredients in layers in greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Season layers with salt and pepper.
Garnish with green pepper slices. Bake at 350° for about 2 hours. Serves 6.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add olives and chilies and heat.
Add 1/2 of each cheese.
Mix enchilada sauce and tomato sauce together.
Dip tortilla in hot oil for a few seconds.
Place one spoonful of mixture and 1 spoonful sauce in middle of tortilla.
Roll up.
Pour remaining sauce and cheeses over top. Heat at 250° until cheese is bubbly and meat is hot.
Makes 12.

title: alice lis' frosted punch
directions: Chill all juices.
Combine juices in a punch bowl.
Add ginger ale by carefully pouring down the side of the bowl to keep carbonation.
Spoon in sherbet.

title: crisp bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions, garlic and green pepper.
Add salt. Cover with ice cubes.
Mix.
Add more ice on top.
Let stand 3 hours, then drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boil and seal.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.
Store in refrigerator.

title: baked beef dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except pecans. Spoon into greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving with crackers.
Makes 4 cups.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix and store tightly covered.
Use 1/3 cup of mixture in 1 cup hot water.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix and cook until thick.
Put in prepared crust and top with lattice top crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop and mix all ingredients.
Fry bacon crisp and break up in mixture.
Make dressing of mayonnaise, small amount of vinegar and sugar to taste.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown and drain the first 3 ingredients.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and then at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple and nuts.
Finally, add bananas.

title: refried beans
directions: When beans (pintos) are done, pour (without juice) into skillet with hot oil.
Mash carefully as you add ingredients.
Add more oil if needed.

title: cranberry pecan salad
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water to dissolve.
Add relish, celery and pecans.
Put half of mixture in 13 x 9-inch dish to chill until firm.
Spread with sour cream; top with remaining gelatin mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: jelly roast
directions: Sprinkle roast liberally with the garlic powder, onion powder, celery salt, meat tenderizer and Worcestershire sauce.
Poke spices into roast with a large fork.
Pour jelly into a small bowl.
Using a pastry brush, coat the roast with jelly.
Let stand for 2 hours. Mix the catsup, oil and 4 tablespoons Worcestershire in a small jar with a lid.
This mixture will separate and must be shaken regularly.
Start roast in the microwave cooking on High power for 6 minutes.
After microwaving, move to grill, basting liberally with the catsup mixture.
Turn every fifteen minutes basting at every turning.
Cook until done.

title: easy buttery rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine all of the ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Spoon into greased muffin tins; fill half full. Bake for 12 to 14 minutes, or until golden.

title: apple dip
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature or microwave 15 seconds on High.
Sift brown sugar and powdered sugar a little at a time into the cream cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Slice apples and dip.

title: spiders candy
directions: In a large bowl, mix Cheerios, noodles and roasted peanuts. Set aside.
In a large saucepan, mix butterscotch chips, marshmallows and butter.
Stir over low heat until melted.
Add cooking oil and beat until smooth.
Add the nuts, noodles and Cheerios and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
You must work fast or the mixture will harden before you're through!

title: creamy chicken manicotti
directions: Heat olive oil in a very large soup kettle or lobster steamer pot.
Add onions and cook over low heat for ten minutes until onions turn clear.
Remove sausage from casing.
Crumble all sausage and ground chuck into pot with olive oil and onions.
Cook until meat is brown.
Drain off as much excess fat as possible.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine the flour and oatmeal in a mixing bowl. Stir in butter, brown sugar and cinnamon until crumbly.
Put 3/4 of the crumbs in a 13 x 9-inch dish and pack down to make crust. Add the raw rhubarb over the crust.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Heat above ingredients to just warm to blend the honey. Steaks should have fat removed and then cross cut.
Pour mixture over steaks and let stand for at least 24 hours, 36 hours is even better.
About every 4 to 6 hours flip over.
If in sealed marinating pan, only need to shake.
Cook on a medium to slow grill until desired doneness.
Slice thinly on the diagonal for tenderness.
Serve with salads and potatoes (baked or salad); makes a real special meal.

title: curry chutney appetizer
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Combine all ingredients and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: apple muffins
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk and stir in melted shortening.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Stir in apples.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: caramel nut acorns
directions: Melt
butter
in
2-quart square casserole pan over low heat. Stir in brown sugar, vanilla
and
1/3 cup pecans.
Add dry ingredients,
mixing
well.
Shape
into
balls
using
a rounded teaspoon.
Flatten on one side.
Pinch top to resemble an acorn. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels and water in
top
of double boiler or microwave.
Dip bottom of acorn in
caramel
1/4 inch deep. Then in crushed pecans.

title: mexicali bean pot
directions: Pour boiling water over navy beans until they are covered by 2-inches of water.
Soak for 1 hour and drain.
Turn drained beans into 4 to 6 quart Dutch oven; add enough boiling water to cover with 2-inches water.
Heat to boiling, cover, reduce heat to a gentle boil for 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.

title: pate
directions: Grind together first four ingredients.
Mix with spices.
Put into earthenware baking dish with brandy and enough veal stock to cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a pan of water at 350°.
Cool.
Keep in refrigerator indefinitely.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Add all ingredients together and cook slowly 2 hours or until thick.

title: doctor bird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch round tube cake pan. Set aside.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix together oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Chill overnight.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Dip tops of balls in plain white sugar or colored sugars for holidays or with cinnamon added to white sugar.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes (or less) in 360° to 375° oven until lightly browned.
These cookies puff up at first then flatten out round with crinkled tops.
Some time ago, these cookies won a Blue Ribbon at the Morgan County Fair.

title: brandi's fabulous cookies
directions: Whisk together flour, rolled oats, salt and baking soda. Cream together in large bowl the margarine, brown sugar and granular sugar; add and mix well the egg and vanilla. Blend all in flour mixture and stir in cranberries and pecans. Drop 1-inch spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 6 to 7 minutes at 350°.

title: polka-dot cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together margarine, peanut butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Add combined flour and baking soda; mix well.
Stir in candies.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage and apple casserole
directions: Cook sausage, drain and set aside.
Pour oil in heavy skillet. Heat at 400° for 5 minutes. Mix corn bread mix, egg and buttermilk.
Stir in sausage.
Pour into heated skillet.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes, then cook pie filling, sugar and cinnamon over low heat and spread over mix.

title: sweet pickles(makes 9 pints.)
directions: Soak in plain water 3 days.
Then cut each pickle in 1/2; put in kettle and cover with cold water with 2 cups vinegar.
Heat 2 hours with grape leaves and alum.
Remove pickles and put in jar and heat vinegar, sugar, 1 oz. allspice whole, blade mace (celery seed and mustard seed).
Heat vinegar 3 mornings.
Fourth morning, can.

title: hot cheese sandwich
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 9-inch greased baking dish, place cheese and ham sandwiches.
Mix together eggs, milk and salt.
Pour egg mixture over sandwiches.
Bake for 1 hour or until tops are golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: pound cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix the margarine, butter and cream cheese. Add the sugar; cream thoroughly. Alternate 2 eggs, 1 cup flour, 2 eggs, 1 cup flour, etc., mixing well after each until all eggs and flour are used.
Add the vanilla.
Grease and flour a tube cake pan.
Put cake in cold oven.
Turn to 300° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: Layer in large bowl 3 cups lettuce.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Layer eggs on lettuce.
Sprinkle with salt, peas, remaining 3 cups of lettuce, bacon and cheese in that order. Spread mayonnaise over and seal to edge of bowl.
Cover and chill 24 hours.
Toss before serving.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: mighty mustang cookies
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter and sugars, Beat in eggs. Combine flour, soda and oatmeal and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fat-free muffins
directions: Mash bananas well; set aside.
Mix together oat bran, liquid, white syrup and egg whites.
Allow to stand at least 10 minutes. Stir in bananas.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix well and chill until ready to serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer the refried beans.
Mix the sour cream and taco seasoning; spread over the beans for the second layer.
Add the cheese, tomato and olives for the third layer.
Serve with taco chips.

title: low calorie bran muffins
directions: Mix and bake in greased muffin pan at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: vegetable ball
directions: Mix cream cheese into other ingredients with fork.
Shape into ball with rubber spatula and roll ball in other half of nuts. Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: overnight sausage egg casserole
directions: Place bread crumbs in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish, sprinkle with cheese and set aside.
Brown sausage over medium heat; drain fat.
Crumble sausage over bread and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard and soup together.
Pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 3 hours before baking.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: play dough recipe
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix wet ingredients together. Blend both batches, then stir over low heat until it forms a ball. Knead a bit.
Let cool.
Store in a plastic container.
Serves 6.

title: turkey and salsa pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Lightly grease cookie sheet. Separate dough into 8 biscuits. Press each biscuit into a 5 1/2-inch circle. Place on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool. Spread each biscuit with 2 tablespoons salsa. Top each with turkey and then shredded cheese. Return to oven; bake for an additional 5 to 7 minutes or until thoroughly heated and cheese has melted. Serve warm.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package except substitute pineapple for water.
Stir coconut into batter.
Grease and flour 2 round pans (8-inch or 9 1/2-inch) or rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake at 350°.
Bake as directed on package.
Cool layers 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Fill and frost with whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: norwegian slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and add salt.
Combine sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar melts.
Let cool.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Mix all in large bowl and toss.
Chill 1 or 2 hours.

title: chicken rice meal
directions: Line the bottom of a 9 x 13 baking dish with buttered bread slices. Combine chicken, mushrooms, rice and cheese. Spoon over bread slices. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over all. Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in order into a casserole dish which has been sprayed with no stick cooking spray.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Steam the carrots in a saucepan for 5 to 6 minutes, until slightly tender. Saute them briefly in the butter in a medium skillet; add the sugar, nutmeg, orange juice and honey. Cook, stirring constantly, until the sugar melts and the carrots are well glazed.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake until slightly brown at 350°.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk, butter, cocoa and salt in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in the rolled oats, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until creamy.
Add egg. Add dry ingredients. Mix.
Form into balls.
Press with glass dipped in sugar each time.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes or until brown on bottom.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flavorings.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add alternately the measured flour and baking powder with milk beginning with flour mixture and ending with flour mixture.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours or until done in preheated 325° oven.

title: spicy applesauce cake
directions: Beat margarine and sugar in bowl until lightly fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add applesauce.
Mix well.
Stir in flour, soda and spices.
Add pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on wire rack.

title: black and blue berry cobbler
directions: In bowl, combine flour, 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine eggs, milk and oil; stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Spread batter evenly onto the bottom of a greased 5-qt. slow cooker.
In a saucepan, combine berries, water, orange peel and remaining sugar; bring to a boil. Remove from the heat; immediately pour over batter.
Cover and cook on high for 2 to 2-1/2 hours or until a toothpick inserted into the batter comes out clean.
Turn slow cooker off.
Uncover and let stand for 30 minutes before serving.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Separate dough into long rectangles.
Place on ungreased 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Press over bottom and sides; seal perforations.
Bake until golden, around 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool completely.
Blend next 6 ingredients until smooth.
Spread evenly over crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Yields 60 appetizers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook macaroni with butter; cook broccoli with butter and salt water.
Drain and put in baking dish.
Add cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 can of milk; grate sharp cheese into it and stir. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake for about 20 minutes or until brown on top.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a bowl.
Combine butter, cocoa and Coca-Cola in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix. Fold in marshmallows.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Ice while hot with Coca-Cola Icing.

title: garlic shrimp and pasta
directions: Mix cornstarch and broth.
Set aside.
In skillet over medium-high heat, heat oil.
Cook shrimp, garlic add pepper until shrimp turn pink, stirring often.
Set shrimp aside.
Add parsley and lemon juice.
Stir cornstarch mixture and add.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Return shrimp to pan.
Heat through.
Toss with pasta.
Serves 6.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cut apples in 1/4-inch slices.
Butter a baking dish.
Add apples and pour water and cinnamon over.
Work together the sugar, butter and flour until crumbly.
Spread it over the apple mixture. Bake uncovered at 375° until light brown.
Serve with ice cream.

title: k. o. soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add other ingredients.
Simmer on low until vegetables are cooked.

title: razorback potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Peel potatoes to uniform size.
Cut each potato, starting at one end into 1/4-inch slices, stopping 1/4-inch from bottom so slices remain attached.
Place potatoes with sliced side up into a well-greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; dot with pieces of butter.
Bake for 20 minutes, basting occasionally with butter in pan.
Mix cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle generously between potato slices and over top.
Bake another 25 to 30 minutes without basting or until golden brown and tender.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt 1/2 of oleo and stir in 1/2 of stuffing mix.
Mix squash with carrots, soup, sour cream and onions.
Pour in baking dish.
Top with remaining oleo and stuffing mix.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: black forest chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 25 minutes in pan and then remove and finish cooling on plate.
Serve with whipped cream and another 21 ounce can of cherries on top of cake.

title: roma blend seasoning mix
directions: Mix; rub this into poultry or pork.
Makes 1/4 cup.

title: teen-agers pasta salad
directions: Cook desired amount of macaroni; drain.
Dice cucumbers and tomato.
Sprinkle with Salad Supreme seasoning.
Add the dressing.

title: banana-brownie sundae
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat 9-inch square baking pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine flour, cocoa, milk powder, baking soda and salt in bowl.
Puree banana, sugar, egg whites, buttermilk and vanilla in food processor until smooth.
Add dry ingredients and pulse just until blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16.
Nutrition information per brownie:
65 calories, 1 gm protein, 0 gm fat, 15 gm carbohydrates, 42 mg sodium, 0 mg cholesterol.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling, salted water according to directions.
While this is cooking, brown beef and onion with basil, thyme and garlic until tender; drain.
Stir in soup, paste, 2 cans water, 1/4 cup of cheese, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Cook on low for 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf; combine spaghetti with sauce and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan and continue baking another 5 minutes.

title: russian dressing for 50
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.

title: self-filled cupcakes(originally from carol bedner)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Sift together the next 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add the next 4 ingredients. Beat until well blended.

title: quick stir-fry
directions: Put oil in hot wok or skillet.
Add broccoli and cook 3 minutes.
Add meat.
Cook until the pinkness is gone.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir-fry for about 4 minutes on high, until everything is hot.
(You may top with toasted sesame seed.) Serve over rice.

title: hash browns casserole
directions: Heat soup, cheese and milk and pour over frozen potatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bibber's corn light bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a greased and floured tube or bundt pan and bake in a slow oven 55 - 60 minutes until browned.

title: cheddar corn muffins
directions: Drain corn, reserving liquid.
Add to melted butter to measure 2/3 cup liquid.
Combine biscuit mix, dry milk and sugar.
Stir in corn and cheese.
Add liquid ingredients and egg.
Mix lightly. Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Remove from pan immediately.

title: mexican meat cups
directions: Roll or pat each biscuit into a 3 1/2 to 4-inch circle. Fit over backs of well-greased muffin pans. Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 9 minutes. Combine meat and sauce in saucepan; heat thoroughly. Remove biscuits from pans; fill with meat sauce. Top with cheese, lettuce and tomatoes. Makes 10.

title: molasses pie
directions: Heat molasses and butter to boiling.
Beat eggs until fluffy, then mix in flour and sugar with the eggs.
Blend well.
Add this to molasses and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: sandwich deluxe
directions: Make sandwich with boiled ham, mustard and cheese.
Use a thin spread of oleo on bread next to cheese.
Dip the sandwich very quickly on each side into a mixture of beaten eggs and milk. Grill or fry, using as little grease as possible.

title: wise's volleyball lasagne
directions: Vegetarian Style:
Substitute zucchini, squash and mushrooms for sausage.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Mix crackers and margarine.
Press in 9 x 13 inch dish and bake.
Cream soft cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in small Cool Whip.
spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding with milk. Pour over cheese layer, chill until set.
Spread large Cool Whip over top.
Can add nuts on top or sprinkle graham crackers on top.

title: crunchy coconut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars gradually.
Cream well.
Beat in egg. Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture with remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Shape into small balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: garden kabobs
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients; set aside. Assemble kabobs by threading meat and vegetables on metal skewers. Place on a cookie sheet.
Pour marinade over kabobs; cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Turn several times.
To cook, grill kabobs over hot coals until the meat and vegetables have reached desired doneness.
Remove from skewers and serve over rice.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: orange punch(serves 60)
directions: Combine juices into the punch bowl. Add orange sherbet. Pour ginger ale over this.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: *You can use 2 1/4 cups self-rising flour.

title: mincemeat
directions: Grind the corned beef.
Measure when done.
Add the same amount of apples.
Cook in a large pot.
Add all the spices.
Just barely cover with water.
Cook until most of the water is gone.

title: company chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pat chicken dry.
Place in bowl.
Pour eggs over.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Drain chicken. Dredge in bread crumbs.
Melt 8 tablespoons butter in skillet over medium heat. Add chicken and cook until just brown (3 minutes on each side). Transfer chicken to glass baking dish.
Melt remaining butter in same skillet.
Add mushrooms and cook until soft, stirring occasionally.
Pour on top of chicken. Top with slices of cheese. Add broth to baking dish.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: french style potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in 1-inch of boiling water. Cover and cook until tender when pierced (about 30 minutes).
Drain.
Let stand for about 10 minutes and cut into 3/8-inch slices.
Place potatoes in a large salad bowl. Add parsley and onion. Blend together mustard, salt, pepper, tarragon, garlic, vinegar and oil.
Pour over potato mixture and toss gently to coat. Cover and let stand at room temperature for at least 3 hours. Chill, if desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour rice in pan; add soups and water and stir.
Place meat on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Do not peek.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Shred 2 or 3 pounds cabbage in electric skillet at boiling. Put glass of water in to prevent cabbage from burning.

title: baked eggs
directions: Butter 6 custard cups.
Break egg in each cup.
Add 1 teaspoon milk to each egg.
Set cups in shallow baking pan.
Pour hot water into pan to depth of 1 inch.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until eggs are firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shoyu chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken thighs.
Mix the ingredients in a pot.
Add chicken and boil for about 1 hour.

title: vinaigrette salad dressing
directions: Whisk together.
Especially good tossed with bibb lettuce.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in heavy skillet; drain off fat. In a large Dutch oven, mix vegetable juice, mushroom soup, ground beef and onions.
Bring to a boil; add mixed vegetables.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: no fail caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter
and slowly add powdered brown sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Stir constantly.	Stir in canned milk and stir until mixture comes
to
a boil.	Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm. Add gradually
powdered
sugar and continue to beat until spreading consistency.

title: chicken pie
directions: Layer chicken in bottom of dish.
Pour broth over chicken. Spread soup over chicken and broth; salt and pepper.
Make mixture of flour, oleo and milk.
Pour over meat mixture; it will be thin. Cook for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft. Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mustard. Cook 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, cheese and milk. Cook slowly until cheese melts. Mix over potatoes well and bake in large flat casserole for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cashew fish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F>
Place butter in a 15x10-1/2x1-1/2-inch jelly-roll pan.
Place pan on center rack of oven for 3 to 4 minutes, until butter melts.
Begin to prepare fush fillets while butter melts.

title: cake from scratch
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in sour milk and vanilla.
Add flour in about 4 equal amounts, blending after each time.
Add bananas and chopped pecans and stir until well blended.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cherry pie filling into 11 x 13-inch pan and spread. Then spread undrained pineapple over the filling.
Spread dry cake mix over that.
Drizzle melted oleo over top.
Sprinkle coconut over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Let set overnight.

title: the ultimate breakfast
directions: Sprinkle raisins over bottom of bowl.
Sprinkle oatmeal over raisins.
Fill (mounded up) bowl with Corn Flakes.
Slice banana lengthwise into 3 equal triangular segments and then slice banana crosswise over Corn Flakes.
Fill with milk to top of bowl; dig in and enjoy.
When half-eaten, you will probably need to add more milk.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Stir in brown sugar. Spread evenly in dish.
Add pineapple.
Spread evenly in dish over the brown sugar.
Sprinkle 4 to 6 tablespoons over pineapple. Pour batter over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until done.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix all together.
You can put coconut or nuts on top, if you want.

title: pancit canton(sauteed egg noodles)
directions: In a deep nonstick pan over medium heat, saute garlic in oil until lightly browned. Add onion, pork, shrimp, carrots, celery, cabbage, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, salt and pepper. Stir while cooking. Cook for 5 to 8 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender. Take out meat and vegetable mixture and set aside.

title: doggie roll-ups
directions: Turn oven to 450°.
Open the can of biscuits and separate them. Then take each biscuit 1 at a time and stretch it.
Make it at least twice as long as it was to begin with.
Cut hot dogs in half; put 1/2 of the hot dog in a biscuit; roll the biscuit around the hot dog and press it closed.
Put it on a cookie sheet.
Do the same with the rest.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: In a bowl, take 2 tablespoons cold mashed potatoes and add powdered sugar, slowly stirring, until it stiffens like pie dough. It will be real thin and watery at first.
Roll it out like thin pie dough and spread peanut butter on it.
Roll it up like a jelly roll.
Cut it into small pieces.
Keep it layered with wax paper in refrigerator.
It's very good and real sweet.

title: country franks
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, cook hot dogs until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Remove hot dogs; set aside.
In same skillet over medium heat, cook peppers and onions in the oil; add seasonings.
Cook until tender, stirring often. Add hot dogs.
Toss gently.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding and milk until stiff. Add condensed milk. Beat again. Add Cool Whip and fold in. Put layer of vanilla wafers in large dish, then layer of bananas, then pudding, then do the 3 layers again. Refrigerate to set. Makes plenty.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into bowl.
Add cheese; mix well. Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add milk; mix well.
Turn onto floured board.
Knead lightly, using as little flour as possible. Roll out 1/2 inch thick; cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 450° oven for about 12 minutes. Makes 14 biscuits.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil. Add eggs and beat well. Add vinegar and food coloring; beat well. Sift dry ingredients. Add alternately with milk. Add vanilla. Beat well. Pour into cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Will make 3 layers.

title: table top pickles
directions: 1st Day:
Slice cukes and cover with salt and water to cover.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Mix crumbs and all 5 spices.
Dip chicken in yogurt, then into crumb mixture.
Brush grill with oil prior to cooking.
Place chicken on grill over medium heat.
Bake for 20 minutes; turn chicken and bake for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Beat Eagle Brand milk slowly.
Add lemon juice.
Dissolve gelatin in as little water as possible.
(No more than 1/4 cup of water.
If too much water, it will make it too watery.)
Add to milk.
Put in baked pie shell.
(I usually let this set if I have time before adding strawberries.)
Slice strawberries and slightly mash in milk.
Not all the way to the crust or crust will be watery.
Top with Cool Whip.
Scrumptious.

title: tacos in pasta shells
directions: Cook pasta shells according to package directions.
Drain and toss with melted butter.
Brown ground beef, stirring to crumble; drain.
Stir in cream cheese, chili powder and salt; simmer 5 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Fill shells with beef mixture. Arrange in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon taco sauce over shells.
Cover and bake 15 minutes.
Uncover; top with cheese and tortilla chips.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with green onions; garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: vanilla glaze
directions: Mix together until it is smooth and creamy.

title: ambrosia spread-fruit dip
directions: Stir together
orange
sections,
cream cheese, coconut and almonds.
Serve with fruit.
Also good used as a spread on Date Nut Roll or Banana Bread.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil 8 potatoes in skins until tender.
Peel and dice. Sprinkle with salt and black pepper.
Brown bacon pieces.
Add onions and saute.
Mix vinegar, water and sugar together.
Pour over bacon-onion mixture in frying pan.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour bacon mixture over diced potatoes.
Serve immediately.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach, drain and squeeze out all water.
Combine all other ingredients with spinach.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Dough can be frozen before baking.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Add crackers and peanut butter.
Stir and pour immediately into a buttered dish.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: macaroni cheese
directions: Cook macaroni about 12 to 14 minutes; drain.
Mix all ingredients well and put in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until bubbles.

title: dry hot chocolate mix
directions: Test before serving and add to taste.
Serve 1/3 mix per mug with hot water.

title: cheese straws
directions: Put 8 oz. cheddar in processor or blender, and turn on.
Add 1/2 of flour, butter, and pepper.
Process all ingredients in food processor until mixture forms a ball.
Then add rest of ingredients a little at a time.

title: christmas casserole(serves 24)
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour and cook until bubbly.
Add milk and stir until thickened.
Add 2 teaspoons salt and 1/2 teaspoon onion salt.
Set aside.
Pour equal amounts of instant rice into two 9 x 13-inch casseroles.
Pour chicken broth and remaining salts over rice.
Sprinkle half of the cheese over rice; top with broccoli and chicken.
Pour cream sauce over all and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds and toast under broiler.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken broth and milk. Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Mix sauce with remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: no fuss lasagna
directions: Brown beef or turkey in a large skillet until no longer pink. Pour off drippings.
Add spaghetti sauce and tomatoes with liquid. Stir to combine and set aside.
In another bowl, combine Ricotta, egg, Parmesan cheese and basil.
Spread 2 cups beef sauce over bottom of 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Add 3 noodles in single layer, pressing into sauce.
Top with all of Ricotta mixture, then 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Add 2 cups beef sauce, then 3 noodles pressed into sauce.
Top with remaining sauce.
Bake 50 minutes or until noodles are fork-tender.
Add remaining Mozzarella on top and tent lightly with aluminum foil.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: creamed tuna
directions: In saucepan, cook celery and onion in oleo until tender. Blend soup slowly.
Add milk; add tuna.
Serve over rice or macaroni.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in baking dish and bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: squash puppies
directions: Combine meal and flour.
Add onion and squash.
Stir in egg and enough milk to make stiff batter.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until brown.

title: fresh vegetable soup
directions: Rinse celery and chop into small pieces.
Measure out 1/2 cup and put aside.
Rinse and scrape carrots and potatoes.
Dice and measure out 1/2 cup of each.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter in large saucepan (use low heat).
Stir; do not burn.
Add all vegetables, except potatoes, to melted butter.
Cook and stir for 10 minutes. Add potatoes.
Cover saucepan and cook 2 minutes.
Add water and bouillon cube.
Boil, uncovered, until vegetables are soft.
Add salt and pepper to please your taste.
Add remaining butter; stir well.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve hot.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt margarine; add crushed egg noodles and brown lightly. Add two cups mixture of beef consomme and water and bring to a boil.
Add rice; cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
Add the chopped vegetables and pimento; cover and simmer another 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: cheese and carrot salad
directions: Blend well and chill.

title: bouquet garni
directions: Tie herbs together with string or thread.
Use according to recipe.

title: broccoli-flower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces.
Layer lettuce in the bottom of large container, then vegetables. Combine mayonnaise and sugar; spread over top of vegetables. Sprinkle with bacon bits and cheese.
Mix just before serving.

title: sex on the beach
directions: Pour over ice and stir.

title: quick butterscotch buns
directions: Soften oleo and mix with sugar.
Spoon butter/sugar mixture into 12 muffin cups, placing about 2 teaspoons in each.
Top with chopped nuts.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Mix baking mix and milk to form soft dough; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Spoon onto mixture in cups.
Bake 10 minutes.
Immediately invert pan on heatproof serving plate.
Leave pan over rolls a few minutes.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: In a soup pot, combine the chicken broth, half and half, potato flakes, 3 1/2 c. cheese and the pepper; mix well. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat and cook for 2-3 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.

title: southern mint julep
directions: Crush mint leaves and sugar in a 12-ounce glass.
Fill with cracked ice and bourbon.
Stir until glass frosts.
Decorate with a sprig of mint.
Very old recipe.

title: taco lasagna
directions: Brown beef in saucepan; drain.
Add taco mix and 1 cup water, stir and simmer 20 minutes.
Cover the bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish with crushed Doritos.
Layer on top of Doritos the chopped peppers, tomatoes, onions, beef and cheeses.
Sprinkle top with crushed Doritos.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with taco sauce.

title: bologna salad
directions: Grate bologna and cheese in large bowl.
Mix relish and mayonnaise into bologna and cheese.
Use enough mayonnaise to make the salad creamy.
Cover and let refrigerate.

title: roasted mustard potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray large flat pan 3 times with Pam. Cut red potatoes into wedges (approximately 4 wedges each), leaving skins on.
Combine mustard, paprika, chili powder and garlic powder in large bowl.
Add potato wedges, tossing to coat evenly.
Put wedges on pan, skin side down.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes, until potatoes are fork-tender.
Serves 4. Per serving:
122 calories, 2 g. fat.

title: mounds candy bar cake
directions: Bake according to package directions.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Pour into unbaked crust and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa very well.
Add egg yolks and milk. Cook 4 minutes in the microwave on Medium-high.
Stop and stir with a wire whisk.
Add butter and vanilla flavoring.
Cook 4 more minutes.
Add mixture to a cool, baked pie crust.
Let pie set 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Cool Whip is optional.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Should be lightly browned on top.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: gummy worm jello
directions: Fix jello as usual in a ring mold. Let cool in refrigerator until thick a little then add the gummy worms. Refrigerate until set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix the soup, mayonnaise, egg, cheese and onion and add this to the drained broccoli. Top with Ritz cracker crumbs (or bread crumbs).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and cabbage
directions: Brown ground beef.
Season to your desire.
Slice cabbage and onion while browning beef.
Drain off grease.
Add cabbage and onion; season again.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: pasta house company special salad and dressing
directions: Put dressing on when ready to serve.

title: cake delight
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Mix 3 eggs, sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Pour over coconut.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together, except 1 cup grated cheese.
Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in mixture and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: texas tornado cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients; beat in eggs and fruit cocktail.
Pour into lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix brown sugar and walnuts together and sprinkle over batter. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Spread icing on cake while hot.

title: zesty french bread
directions: Brush cut side of bread with dressing; top with cheese and basil.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese begins to melt.
Cut into 2-inch slices.
Yields 16 servings.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, 1 1/2 cups milk, sugar and salt in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thick and creamy, 15 to 20 minutes.
Blend remaining 1/2 cup of milk and egg.
Stir into rice mixture.
Add raisins.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon, if desired.

title: tropical fruit cake
directions: Place in pan in order listed.
Cover with pecans. Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon herb marinated chicken
directions: In cup mix first 5 ingredients; pour over chicken.
Cover; let stand at room temperature no longer than 30 minutes, turning once. Broil 10 minutes or until thoroughly cooked, turning once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Finely grind oats in processor.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Blend well.
With electric mixer, beat together butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Fold in pecans, semi-sweet chocolate and milk chocolate.
Form dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Space 2 inches apart.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Crust Preparation:
Crush the Ritz crackers.
Add margarine and sugar.
Retain 1/2 cup of crumbs for topping.
Use rest to line the bottom and sides of a bowl or cake pan.

title: squash, tomato and pepper relish
directions: Put into pan and cook until tender, then taste.
Add salt, pepper and any other seasonings as desired.
Put in oven at 500° to allow some of the juice to disappear, then jar.

title: aunt ruthie's dessert
directions: Combine flour and sugar and cut in butter.
Add nuts.
Press into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Drain pineapple; reserve 1 tablespoon juice. Combine tablespoon juice, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Fold in crushed pineapple and fruit cocktail and spread over crust.
Set overnight.
Mmmm Good!

title: rice hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix and put into a baking dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Stir occasionally.
During the last 15 minutes, sprinkle the top with Chinese noodles.

title: olive branch chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine lemon juice, ginger, garlic, salt and pepper.
Place chicken in marinade; turn to coat.
Cover and marinate; refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Prepare grill or preheat oven for broiling.
Remove chicken from marinade; place in broiling pan.
Rub with oil; sprinkle with curry powder and cayenne.
Grill or broil 6 to 8 inches from heat source until meat is cooked through (8 to 10 minutes per side).

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add margarine.
Mix eggs and milk; beat slightly and combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange chicken and stuffing
directions: Brown chicken in margarine in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Move chicken to side of skillet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top each piece with orange slice.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients. Store in container with tight lid. Use 1/4 cup for each cup of boiling water.

title: sunshine fruit dip
directions: In medium bowl, stir together all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 1 3/4 cups dip.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes.
Use glass dish (Pam).
Add potatoes; sprinkle with butter, Parmesan cheese, Romano cheese and seasoned salt. Sprinkle until coated.
Broil until golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash; add onion, salt, sugar, pepper, margarine and soup.
Mix well.
Pour half squash mixture into greased baking dish.
Put half crackers over this and half the cheese.
Finish with squash mixture and crackers and top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry snack cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour and sugar. Cut in butter until crumbly. Set aside 3/4 cup for topping. Add the baking powder, milk and egg yolks to remaining mixture; mix well. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; fold into batter. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with blueberries and reserved crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown and a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Yield: 15 to 18 servings.

title: scum salad
directions: Drain juice off pineapple; mix all ingredients together.
Can add cottage cheese if you want it.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: You will need cupcake liners.

title: chicken nacho casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips and cheese.
Spray pan with Pam.
Line with chips.
Dip 1/2 mixture over chips.
Layer chips again and add remaining mix.
Bake at 400° until hot through and through.
Add grated cheese and serve.

title: braised fennel
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a small baking dish.
Trim off any tough stalks and bottom from fennel.
Add trimmed fennel and lemon juice to boiling salted water.
Cook 10 minutes; drain. Place boiled fennel in buttered dish; add hot stock.
In a small bowl, combine bread crumbs, cheese, lemon peel, salt and pepper. Sprinkle over boiled fennel.
Bake in preheated oven 30 to 35 minutes or until fennel is tender and topping is golden brown. Makes 2 servings.

title: banana oatmeal cookies(diabetic)
directions: Cream together margarine, egg and sweetener.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: potato beef soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook ground beef in water. Add onions and potatoes. In a separate saucepan, heat soup and milk together. When potatoes are tender, add soup mixture.
Season to taste. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: old-fashioned custard pie
directions: Beat slightly with a rotary egg beater the eggs; then beat in sugar, salt and milk.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top of pie.
Bake 40 minutes at 450° for first 15 minutes.
Lower oven to 350° and finish baking for remaining time.

title: almond delight
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter; add nuts, coconut, flour and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Spread out on cookie sheet and bake 15 or more minutes, until golden brown.
Remove from oven and let cool.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix well.
Make meat balls and put in casserole dish.
Saute in bacon fat the pepper and onion.
Add tomato soup and water. Pour over meat balls.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: impossible ham and cheese pie
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Place chopped ham in bottom of pie plate.
Add shredded Swiss cheese on top of ham and chopped onion. In blender, add milk, eggs and Bisquick.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour over mixture and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon in small bowl.
To juice, add baking powder and set aside.
Mix salmon, egg and onion until sticky.
Stir in flour.
Add juice and baking powder.
Mix, make out patties and fry until golden brown.

title: stewed tomato salad
directions: Heat tomato soup in a pan.
Stir in and dissolve Jell-O in hot tomato soup.
Add water.
Stir in lemon juice.
Pour into dish and congeal.

title: peach rhubarb jam
directions: In a large bowl, combine rhubarb and sugar. Allow to stand overnight.
Transfer to a large saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: fudge pies
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hopscotch candy
directions: Melt chips over hot water in a double boiler, then stir in peanut butter.
Mix in noodles and marshmallows in a large bowl. Add butterscotch mixture and mix thoroughly.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper, chill until sets.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix together all ingredients and spread on 1/2 buns; broil 5 minutes or until golden brown (doesn't take long!).
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: rafferty's potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook potatoes and onion in water until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add cream cheese until melted.
Add rest of ingredients and serve hot.

title: salad delight
directions: Mix mayonnaise, Parmesan and sugar together.
Put all ingredients together and refrigerate for 1 hour in advance.

title: party special chicken salad
directions: Stew and pull meat from chickens or use enough parts to equal 2 whole chickens.
May select parts to taste, but remember, too much white meat will make your salad dry.
Cut up by hand into fine bits.
Cut up celery, pickles and hard-boiled eggs.
Mix together with mayonnaise (may use fat-free).
Season to taste. Keep refrigerated.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Season chicken lightly with salt and pepper.
Wrap each piece with a strip of bacon.
Blend soup and sour cream.
Line up chicken in a large shallow, lightly buttered baking dish or pan, putting 2 or 3 slices of dried beef under each piece of chicken. Pour sour cream mixture over it.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: date nut bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well. Put in greased and floured 9 x 15 x 3-inch pan in cold oven at 300°.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 12-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm.
May freeze after baking.

title: mama jack's rolls
directions: Put yeast in 1/4 cup warm water; let set awhile.
Add other 2 3/4 cups warm water or water from cooked potatoes.
Mix all ingredients well, then add the flour; knead.
Put in greased bowl and let set until it doubles in size.
Put on floured board and knead.
Put in muffin pan (greased) and let rise again. Bake at 350° until golden brown.
After cooked, take them out of oven and butter the tops.

title: baseball party punch
directions: Add 7-Up until bowl is filled, may take only 6 to 7 bottles.

title: lazy pie
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and beat to a smooth batter.
Pour this into casserole.
Pour in the fruit on top of the batter.
Bake at 350° until batter, which rises to the top, is brown.
This serves 6 people.

title: lasagne
directions: Boil noodles in water.
Brown beef and onion; add remaining ingredients.
Put small amount of meat sauce on the bottom of the pan.
Layer noodles, meat sauce, grated Cheddar cheese, grated Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: party pork
directions: Coat pork with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in oil in large skillet.
Add celery, green pepper, onion, pineapple, catsup, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: lean creamy potatoes
directions: You will also need vegetable cooking spray.

title: italian crescent casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown beef with onion.
Drain.
Stir in sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Heat until hot.
Combine Mozzarella cheese and sour cream.
Pour hot meat mixture into
ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon cheese mixture over meat.
Separate crescent rolls into 2 rectangles.
Place side by side over cheese mixture.
Combine Parmesan cheese and margarine.
Crumble evenly over dough.
Bake for 18 to 25 minutes until deep golden brown. Cut into squares to serve.

title: spiced carrots(serves 12)
directions: Drain onions.
Save juice.
Cut pepper into small pieces. Pare, slice and cook carrots.

title: pork chops with stuffing
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Place in shallow dish.
Place a mound of stuffing on each pork chop.
Blend soup and water; pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Combine margarine and graham cracker crumbs.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then layer over the crust:
coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and crushed walnuts.
Pour condensed milk over the top evenly and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: twice as nice rice salad
directions: *Use any combination of the following chopped or shredded vegetables:
carrots, cucumbers, green pepper, mushrooms, radishes, tomato or zucchini.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Combine chocolate pieces and peanut butter in large microwaveable dish.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate over cereal, stirring until all the pieces are evenly coated.
Pour cereal mixture into a plastic bag with powdered sugar.
Shake and spread on wax paper to cool.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix milk and baking mix into soft dough in bowl.
Roll into rectangle 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick on floured surface.
Brush dough with margarine.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over dough. Roll as for jelly roll from long side.
Slice dough 1-inch thick. Place cut side down in 9 or 10-inch baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add pineapple juice, nuts and oranges.
Chill.

title: cheese bread hors d'oeuvres
directions: Seed and chop chilies.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Spread on bread slices.
Freeze.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: japanese style spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into serving size pieces.
Place in baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over spareribs.
Let marinate for one hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add cheese and tomatoes; mix until smooth. Add beans, sour cream and burrito mix.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: crispy oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Stir in brown sugar.
With a spoon, blend in margarine, egg and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly after each addition.
Mix in oats, raisins and pecans.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Dip tops of balls in sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheet 3 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until tops are brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: turkey chili con carne
directions: Combine turkey and onions in Dutch oven.
Brown.
Drain fat. Add all other ingredients to the meat and onions.
Stir to blend. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Good by itself or over rice or baked potato.

title: annie's fruit salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in large container, adding all juices from fruit.
Take 1 large box of strawberry Jell-O and prepare as directed on box.
Pour over fruit.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and cocoa together and set aside. Blend shortening, sugar and eggs together at high speed. Gradually add milk alternately with dry ingredients.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet and bake 8 or 9 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and place 1/2 large marshmallow in center of each cookie.
Return to oven and bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Remove from sheet.
Cool and ice.
Makes 9 dozen cookies.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk.
Beat slowly for 1 minute until blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and drain.
Combine half and half, eggs and salt.
Mix well.
Layer bread, sausage and cheese in a 10 x 15-inch baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over layers. Chill overnight, covered.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 12.

title: burmese red curry(a simple yet popular burmese dish, known as see-piyan)
directions: Combine chicken or beef with all ingredients, except water. Cook covered over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Remove lid and braise meat over medium-low heat, with a wooden spoon for another 10 minutes.
The key is to braise the meat very well.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar. Blend in.
Cover with plastic or foil and chill.
Roll out on lightly floured board or between two sheets of floured wax paper. Cut into fancy shapes with a cookie cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Sprinkle with plain or colored sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 8 minutes, or until very light brown.

title: frozen punch
directions: Dissolve Jello in 9 cups of boiling water.
Bring to boil 4 cups sugar and 4 cups of water; boil until dissolved.
Add Jello mixture, lemon juice, and pineapple juice.
Freeze in any kind of containers.
Take out of the freezer 1 1/2 hours before serving. When ready to serve, put softened frozen mixture into punch bowl. Pour ginger ale over the mixture.
Stir and serve.
Makes a slush punch.

title: hot seafood salad
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Mix lightly. Pour into casserole and sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients well and drop from teaspoon into deep, hot shortening.
Fry until brown.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake per package instructions.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Melt caramels with milk and butter.
Sprinkle chocolate chips, pecans and caramel mixture over partially baked batter, then pour the rest of the batter on top.
Bake 25 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream if desired.

title: rice and consomme
directions: Melt the margarine, then add the onion, rice and beef consomme soup.
Pour into baking dish.
Place seasoned chicken or pork chops on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cioppino
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and saute scallions, pepper, leeks, garlic, onion and parsley.
Then add bay leaves, rosemary, thyme, all tomato stuff, wine, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and simmer 1 hour.

title: country supper casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in oil.
Drain.
Place in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Put salt and pepper and one can of tomato sauce over meat.
Arrange beans and carrots over meat.
Spoon mashed potatoes around edge of casserole.
Pour one can of tomato sauce over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until potatoes are brown.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: ice cream muffins
directions: Mix together.
Put into paper lined muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes at 425°.

title: chocolate marshmallow slices
directions: In medium saucepan over low heat, melt butter and chocolate chips, stirring constantly until blended.
Remove from heat; cool 5 minutes.
Stir in marshmallows; add 1 cup nuts.
Do not allow marshmallows to melt.
On wax paper, shape mixture into two 7-inch logs.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate 20 minutes.
Roll in more nuts and refrigerate overnight; wrap in foil.
Cut rolls into 1/4-inch slices.
Store in a covered container in a cool dry place.
Makes about 3 dozen slices.

title: fresh fruit salad(30 servings)
directions: Slice or cube all fruit, except grapes.
Mix sugar with cherry pie filling, then add to other fruit in large bowl.
Stir until mixed.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours before serving.

title: cookies and cream smoothie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender. Process until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage in baking dish.
Brown beef and onion.
Stir in rice.
Place the mixture on top of the cabbage.
Season with salt and pepper. Combine soup and water.
Pour over the other ingredients.
Cover.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and melted butter together and place in 13 x 9-inch pan to form crust.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs in a bowl.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat on low speed until smooth.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Middle will appear soft, but will set up when cool.
This makes its own crust.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Put in casserole.
Top with sliced, hard-boiled eggs and crushed potato chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly coat a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine first six ingredients; set aside.
In another large bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Add bananas, buttermilk, applesauce and vanilla. Stir into dry ingredients until just blended.
Add nuts.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 45 to 55 minutes or until golden.
Serves 12.
Calories per serving 215, grams of fat 3.6, 0 mg cholesterol.

title: rancher's baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and onions until done. Combine all ingredients. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruited holiday bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, beat butter or margarine, brown sugar and vanilla. Add flour and baking soda, beating until blended.
Stir in pineapple, cherries, raisins or dates and walnuts.
Spread mixture evenly in greased baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.
Do not overbake.
Surface should be slightly soft.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Drain first 5 ingredients separately.
Mix sour cream and celery soup.
In casserole dish, put layer of beans, layer of mixture, layer of corn, layer of mixture, etc., until all have been used.
Melt oleo. Add crackers and mix.
Sprinkle over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: watermelon sherbet treat
directions: Soften lime sherbet and line the bowl (very deep-like Tupperware lettuce keeper).
Freeze until firm.
Soften raspberry sherbet and blend in the chocolate chips.
Fill in the center of the container.
Freeze until firm (allow several hours).
Remove from freezer.
Let stand a few minutes.
Unmold onto plate and slice.

title: southern fried chicken and gravy
directions: Rinse and dry chicken pieces.
Dredge in flour, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Heat about 2-inches corn oil in a large frying pan.
Add chicken to the pan and fry, covered, 5 minutes.
Continue frying uncovered until that side is nicely browned.
Turn chicken pieces; cover and fry 5 minutes.
Remove cover and continue frying until brown.
The chicken should be turned only once.
Drain chicken on paper towel and keep warm while making gravy.

title: cheesy beef bake
directions: Mix hamburger and sauce.
Put layer of plain noodles, hamburger and then cheese.
Repeat until everything is used.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Parboil the sweet potatoes and reserve 1 cup of the liquid. Combine the liquid with the sugar, salt, cornstarch, butter and vanilla.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Line a baking dish with the cooked, peeled and sliced sweet potatoes and pour liquid mixture over them.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: spaghetti with meatball sauce
directions: Put slices of bread in a bowl; cover with water.
Let soak a minute or two.
Squeeze water out of the bread.
Mix the soft bread with ground beef, Parmesan cheese, egg, chopped parsley, onion, garlic, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly and shape into small balls.

title: cocoa pecan meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Beat egg whites, vanilla, cream of tartar and salt at high speed until soft peaks form.
Beat in sugar, a few tablespoons at a time, until meringue is stiff and shiny.
Sift cocoa on top of meringue and carefully fold into mixture.
Fold in ground pecans.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Place a pecan half on top of each meringue.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until firm and dry.
Remove from sheets and cool on wire racks.
Yield:
Approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Melt sugar, milk and oleo in pan. Mix cornstarch and milk. Add to other mixture; heat but not boil. Add to baked pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake 10 minutes.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Spread margarine on bottom of 8 x 8-inch or similar size casserole.
Layer potatoes across bottom of pan.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and garlic powder over potatoes.
Dot with margarine.
Add additional layer of potatoes, spices and margarine.
Repeat until potatoes are used.
Sprinkle paprika across top of potatoes. Cover with Saran Wrap.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Take off cover and place in oven for 10 minutes.

title: cooked frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Cool.
When cool, add and beat with a mixer the sugar, oleo and vanilla until stiff and then frost your favorite cake with it.

title: black beans-cuban style
directions: Soak black beans overnight in cold water.
In morning, rinse beans and cover with fresh water in crock-pot.
Add all ingredients except salt, pepper and vinegar.
Cook until tender, then season with salt and pepper.
Add vinegar and cook for 1/2 hour more.
Serve over white rice.

title: creole cauliflower
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add onion and green pepper and brown lightly.
Blend in flour, stirring, then add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling point and cook three minutes, stirring constantly.
Add cauliflower and heat through. Place mixture in casserole, top with cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts and is lightly browned.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown meat; season with salt, pepper and a little garlic salt. Drain fat.
Add ketchup or barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar. Roll out dough.
Place rolled dough into greased muffin cups, making sure dough goes up the sides.
Fill with cooked meat mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: grill potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into thick wedges, leaving skin on.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Brush mixture on potatoes.
Brown 15 minutes on each side.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Use a 10 x 18-inch pan, greased and floured.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in large unbaked 9 5/8 pie shell or two small pie shells for 40 minutes.

title: chicken jubilee
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Drizzle with butter.
Broil until brown.
Combine sauce, drained peaches and cherries, sliced onion and chili sauce.
Spoon over chicken. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook beets and prepare or drain canned beets.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and stir well.
Place over medium heat. Stir until clear and thickened.
Add butter.
Add beets.
Simmer a few minutes so flavor penetrates the beets.
Excellent hot or cold as relish with turkey, chicken or pork.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring rice to boil; cook 7 minutes. Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla to creamy mixture. Add drained rice. Stir well; cool. Add nutmeg. Serves 6 to 8.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Melt butter or margarine and mix in package of Italian Dressing.
Mix frozen peas, mushrooms, and water chestnuts.
Add seasoning & butter mixture to pea mixture and stir.
Bake at 350° 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in pan; add water.
In small bowl, mix sugar, flour and margarine.
Sprinkle over apples.
Sprinkle on cinnamon. Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook 40 minutes.
Best when served warm.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Mix sausage (or ham) with herbs and shape into 8 round patties.
Wrap meat around the hard-boiled eggs.
Roll eggs in flour seasoned with salt and pepper, then in beaten eggs and bread crumbs.
Deep fry in hot fat until sausage is cooked or bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Bake ham covered eggs in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.
I add a beaten egg to ham mixture to help hold it together.
To serve, cut eggs in quarters lengthwise.

title: grammaw clark's oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together first 6 ingredients until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter; press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients with electric mixer; pour over cake mix crust.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until light brown. Let cool before cutting.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix thawed whipped topping and Eagle Brand milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill (or freeze in any mold or dish).

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, baking powder and salt in a bowl. Add eggs, coffee, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes (batter will be thin).
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with your favorite vanilla frosting.

title: quick and easy pork chow mein
directions: In a large skillet, combine pork, celery, onion, green pepper, bouillon, sugar, pepper, 1 1/2 cups water and soy sauce. Cover and bring to a boil. Simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir in bean sprouts.
In a small bowl, combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup water until smooth.
Over medium-high heat, carefully add to skillet the cornstarch mixture, stirring constantly, until thickened. Serve over chow mein noodles or rice.

title: georgia cornbread
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, then sour cream.
Add corn and vanilla; mix in cornmeal, salt and baking powder.
Bake until golden brown at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Let it boil for one minute.
Then add remainder of ingredients.
Mix and spoon out onto wax paper.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Mix cookies and butter together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan and chill for 1 hour.
Spoon ice cream over crust and then sprinkle with peanuts.
Place in freezer.

title: christmas breakfast casserole (church eggs)
directions: Butter and cube bread.
Place cubes into large oblong pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Place sausage over bread.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over bread and sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
(Can be frozen at this point.)
Bake unfrozen at 350° for 1 hour.
(Hence the name Church Eggs; can be baked while at church with timer.)
Frozen may bake 15 minutes longer.

title: favorite meat loaf(microwave)
directions: In a small bowl, combine tomato sauce, brown sugar and mustard;
set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs, onion, cracker crumbs, ground beef, salt and pepper. Add 1/2 cup tomato sauce mixture and stir.
Place meat mixture in a glass ring mold or a 2-quart microwave-safe round casserole; pour remaining tomato sauce mixture over top of meat.
Cook on High in microwave, uncovered, for 12 to 14 minutes; remove and let stand (covered) for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: five minute casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, layer rice, then corn, then ground beef (crumbled).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour tomato sauce over meat.
Cover dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Put cake mix and pudding together dry.
Add oil, eggs and cold water.
Beat 10 minutes.
Bake in oblong pan 35 minutes at 350°. When baked punch holes in cake with fork while still warm.
Spoon mixture over cake letting juice slowly go into holes in the cake.

title: golden grahams s'mores
directions: Grease pan 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Heat syrup, butter and chips to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Pour over cereal in bowl.
Toss until coated.
Fold in marshmallows 1 cup at a time.
