Press in pan.
Let stand 1 hour; cut into squares.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Beat eggs; add to mixture.
Crush vanilla wafers fine and add alternately with milk; beat.
Add nuts and coconut.
Stir.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
If oven gets too hot, reduce heat.

title: chicken beer bake
directions: Flour chicken breasts; brown in oil.
Put browned chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine soup, soy sauce, almonds, beer and mushrooms in a large bowl; beat together, then pour over the chicken.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste occasionally.
This is good served with rice.

title: creamed ham
directions: Melt oleo, add flour and blend well.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients; cook until slightly thickened and cheese is melted.
Serve on toast, rice or potatoes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: never fail frosting
directions: Boil all but vanilla 1 full minute.
Add vanilla.
Let cool until almost cold.
Then beat and spread on cake.

title: crab dip
directions: Drain crab meat; mix all ingredients together well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate for 2-3 hours.

title: jiffy black walnut cake
directions: Place all ingredients in electric mixer bowl in order given. Beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Don't chop nuts in advance.
The mixer will do it for you.

title: thrifty meat balls
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Shape into meat balls.
Brown in skillet, turning until browned.
Use 1 can of cream of mushroom soup and 1 can of water to cook meat balls 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sausage casserole 2
directions: Brown sausage and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Boil egg noodles. Drain.
Mix milk and soups together.
Add sausage mixture and noodles to the milk and soup.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be topped with cracker crumbs.

title: icing
directions: Cream shortening and butter.
Add vanilla.
Add powdered sugar 1 cup at a time.
After sugar is mixed in, add milk and beat until fluffy.

title: chicken macaroni salad
directions: Drain the pineapple chunks and fruit cocktail.
Shred the chicken.
Mix all the ingredients together.

title: nanny's candy
directions: Mix and dissolve sugar and syrup, but do not boil.
Add peanut butter to sugar mixture; stir.
Add cereal and coconut.
Mix thoroughly and put in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish or large cookie sheet.
Heat tidbits in double boiler; spread on candy.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Mix together and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: skillet squash casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low heat.

title: sausage swirl
directions: Prepare biscuit mix according to directions on package.
Roll dough out.
Sprinkle sausage (raw or precooked) over the dough. Roll into a 3-inch roll (jelly-roll style).
Put into freezer for about 30 minutes.
Remove from freezer and slice into 1/4-inch pieces.
Put on slightly greased baking sheet and cook at 350° or until brown (approximately 15 minutes).

title: derby fruit dip
directions: Cream together and chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and add sherbet.
Mix well and serve.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in covered casserole dish at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
For the last 10 minutes, uncover to brown to the top.

title: finger jello
directions: In a bowl, mix all gelatin together.
Add boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares or use your favorite cookie cutter.
Kids love this.

title: chicken imperial
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Put chicken into greased baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: my mom's pickled beets and red beet eggs
directions: Select beets of uniform size.
Wash and cut off greens, but allow at least 1-inch of stem to remain to prevent bleeding and loss of sweetness and color.
Cook beets in enough water to completely cover beets until tender.
(Young beets will require about 1/2 hour.)
When tender, plunge into cold water.
Rub skins off with fingers.
Do not cut into soft beet.

title: fresh fruit drinks
directions: Blend fruits until smooth in blender.
Ice can be added to blender to make drink a sherbet-like dessert.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and place in casserole dish.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Break angel food cake into pieces and place in dish or pan. Then mix instant pudding mix and pour over broken pieces of cake. Then place pudding mix over this and then add Cool Whip to top. Chill and serve.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Combine the soups, tomatoes and chicken broth to make a sauce. In a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, layer the ingredients in the following order:
chicken, Doritos, onion, cheese and sauce. Repeat once more and top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Freezes well.

title: watergate salad
directions: Add pudding and pineapple juice; mix well.
Fold in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Add 1/2 cup nuts, if desired. Spread in container and chill.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sugar, oil and apricot nectar.
Beat in eggs.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour. Mix powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Spread on baked cake and place under broiler until melted.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in a skillet until brown.
Drain. Stir in taco season mix.
Spread in plate and sprinkle with chilies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, about 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour on top of hamburger, onion and chilies.
Bake at 400° about 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Top with tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes and shredded lettuce if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Melt butter.
Add to graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 into 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Set aside.
Mix Dream Whip, Pet milk and vanilla.
Beat until stiff.
Add Dream Whip mixture to cream cheese mixture; mix well.
Spread 1/2 of this on top of graham crackers; next layer, can of cherry pie filling. Finish layering with cream cheese mix.
Top with remaining graham crackers.

title: hot pecan dip
directions: Toast pecans in butter and salt in oven.
Watch closely.
Mix next 9 ingredients and lastly fold in sour cream.
Place in buttered 8-inch pie tin.
Arrange pecans on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.
Freezes well.
Freeze before baking.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel, slice and cook carrots until tender.
Drain and cool carrots.
Heat soup, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and oil. Chop pepper and onion.
Mix peppers and onions into carrots. Pour soup mixture over carrot mixture and stir.
Serve warm or cold.

title: mound bars
directions: Melt butter and mix ingredients in order except chocolate and paraffin wax.
Spread.
Refrigerate 2 hours or freezer 45 minutes.

title: bride's pink punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Dissolve drink mix in cold water.
Add sugar and stir well.
Add juice and gelatin. Refrigerate.
Add 7-Up and sherbet just before serving.
Serves 35.

title: kids spaghetti
directions: In medium saucepan, brown onion in oil.
Add sliced franks (pan-fry).
Add ketchup and water.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Cook spaghetti as directed.
Mix sauce and spaghetti well.
Serve warm.

title: layered party salad
directions: Tear spinach into pieces.
In the bottom of a large glass or wooden salad bowl, spread the spinach.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Add a layer of finely chopped egg, a layer of ham, a layer of torn or shredded lettuce and sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Scatter peas over all.
Thinly slice onion; pull onion slices into rings and spread on salad.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise; spread evenly over top.
Arrange cheese over all. Cover bowl with plastic wrap; refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, sprinkle with bacon.
Do not toss.
Serve portions all the way to the bottom of bowl.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix and cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift twice: flour, tartar, soda and salt.
Mix together with creamed ingredients.
Flatten on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: romantic torte(cake)
directions: Pour hot water over baking soda and dates; cool and set aside. Cream shortening.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; mix well. Alternate flour and date mixture into the batter; mix well.
Place 2/3 of batter in Bundt pan; sprinkle with 1/2 of the nuts and Kisses (or bars, broken up).
Pour the rest of the batter on top; top with remaining nuts and Kisses.
Bake for 1 hour, or until brown.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix dry mustard and vinegar and let stand for 1 hour.
Add beaten egg yolk and sugar.
Cook over medium heat in saucepan until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool and add mayonnaise.
This will keep refrigerated for a long time.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and both cans of soup until onion is done. Then layer saltines, squash and cheese, two or three layers, in dish.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese has melted.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt and spices.
Add oil, eggs and milk.
Last add apples and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan or regular size cake pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate-topped banana split dessert
directions: Spread graham cracker crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour melted margarine over crumbs.
Prepare pudding mix using package directions.
Layer pudding, pineapple, banana slices and whipped topping in prepared dish.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Arrange cherries on top.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Chill until serving time.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: mom's in a hurry cheese soup
directions: Mix ingredients together in pot.
Heat slowly.

title: stuffed filet of sole(baked)
directions: Wash and drain fish.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Divide filling evenly for the 8 fillets.
Spread filling on each piece and roll from narrow end.
If necessary, hold together with toothpicks. Place fish in greased shallow baking pan.
Cover with tomato sauce. Cut lemon slices very thin.
Place one on top of each fillet.
Bake at 450° for about 12 to 15 minutes or unti fish is flaky to touch. Do not overcook!

title: pistachio salad
directions: Drain the pineapple and mix all ingredients together.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Place peaches in shell.
Pour over them the cream mixture. Don't beat cream!
Mix cream, flour, sugar and salt together with spoon.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: grits souffle
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients over moderate heat.
Stir next 2 ingredients into grits. Remove from heat. Stir in eggs.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch casserole (or any large enough casserole). Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Better if made early in a.m. or day before. Bake at dinnertime.
Great with ham.

title: a popo's almond cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together and beat until fluffy.
Add oil, almond extract, baking soda and salt.
Mix in flour.
Roll dough into round balls and make indentation with a finger.
Place almond or a dot of red dye in indentation.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: danish pastry apple bars
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour and salt; cut in Crisco.
Beat egg yolk in measuring cup and add enough milk to make 2/3 cup liquid; mix well.
Stir egg mixture into flour mixture.
On floured surface, roll 1/2 dough to fit 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch baking pan and place dough in pan.
Sprinkle with corn flakes; top with apples. Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Roll remaining dough to make top crust.
Place over apples and seal edges.
Cut slits in top dough for escape of steam.
Beat egg white until frothy and spread on top.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes. While still warm, drizzle with glaze.
Cut in bars.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and Crisco.
Stir until Crisco is dissolved and cool mixture to lukewarm.
Add yeast, which has been dissolved in lukewarm water and the egg; mix well. Stir in flour to make a soft dough.
Rub surface with Crisco; cover and store in refrigerator.
Will keep about 1 week.

title: hominy corn
directions: Put corn and soda in a big, clean wash pot.
Fill with water and build fire around pot.
Boil and keep adding water as it cooks.
Stir the corn real often to try to keep from sticking. Cook until tender.
Dip corn from the pot and drain water off. Put in enamel pans and wash until water is clear.
Get the black eyes out while washing.
Pack in clean jars and cook in pressure canner for 20 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.
Do not put in freezer.

title: mother's dumplings
directions: In large mixing bowl, add flour.
Cut in shortening and add milk to form dough.
Roll out
onto
floured surface.
Cut into strips.
Bring broth, soup and bouillon
cubes to a boil. Drop in strips, one at a time.
Reduce
heat.
Never stir; you must shake the dumplings.

title: creamed vegetables
directions: In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper; cook until mixture is smooth and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Stir in vegetables; cook until thoroughly heated.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch dish with margarine.
Cook broccoli and drain well.
Make layers of broccoli, flour, thin pats of margarine, salt, pepper and Velveeta cheese strips. Continue layers until dish is full.
Pour 1 cup of milk over casserole.
Then crush 2 cups crackers and 1 stick margarine.
Mix crackers and margarine.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried rice with shrimp, pork, ham or chicken
directions: Stir-fry pork in skillet sprayed with Pam.
Push aside and stir-fry carrots, garlic and onion.
Push aside with meat and stir-fry egg whites.
Mix with other ingredients in skillet.
Add peas, cooked rice and soy sauce.
Mix together until heated. Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican corn muffins
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Add wet ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into muffin tin sprayed with PAM.
Bake at 350 degrees approximately 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Break up lumps of cake mix with whisk.
Add eggs and 1/3 cup milk and stir by hand just until moist.
Pat 1/2 of this mixture in pan.
Reserve remainder.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
Combine caramels and remaining 1/3 cup milk.
Microwave at 70% power, stirring every 1 1/2 minutes for 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Remove pan from oven.
Sprinkle Toll House chips on top.
Gently flow caramel mixture on chocolate.
Make "patties" from remaining dough and lay on top of caramel.
Return to oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool on rack for 1 hour.
Cover and refrigerate overnight to set caramel.

title: maple walnut pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugars until fluffy.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat into butter mixture alternately with combined milk and maple flavoring.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Mix in walnuts.
Turn into greased 9 or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in lower third of 300° oven for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes until tests done.
Turn out onto rack to cool. Drizzle with Maple Glaze and garnish with walnuts.

title: pea picking cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, Mandarin oranges and Crisco oil together; mix well.
Cook in layer pans.
Let the layers cool thoroughly. Stir Cool Whip, vanilla pudding mix and crushed pineapple; spread on cake.
Put in refrigerator awhile before serving it.
It is good!

title: brown sugar pecan bars
directions: Melt margarine in a bowl.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in flour.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Stir well. Batter will be stiff.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: my own chocolate covered nut clusters
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and milk in deep saucepan.
Stir fast with spoon until well mixed.
Cook without stirring until mixture boils up 4 times (each time remove from heat) or until forms a soft ball when dropped into water.
Remove from heat; stir fast.
Add chocolate and stir until almost melted.
Add nuts and raisins and stir until it takes shape and loses gloss.
Pour into greased pan or drop off from the spoon on wax paper.
Let cool (if poured into pan, break into pieces after cooled).

title: buckeye balls
directions: Line a baking sheet with wax paper.
Mix peanut butter, vanilla and sugar together with hands to form stiff dough.
If using food processor, add a bit of melted butter to adhere.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Refrigerate on wax paper for at least 3 hours.

title: quick dip
directions: Melt caramels in microwave after they have been unwrapped. Add sour cream and mix thoroughly.
You may add some cinnamon. Place in dip bowl surrounded by sliced apples.
Just wash and core apples; slice in average slices.
You may use other fruit.
It makes a delicious appetizer, after school snack or snack while watching the TV.

title: red clam sauce and linguine by hunt's
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in oil in skillet.
Add clams and their juice, Hunt's tomato paste, water, lemon juice, parsley, sugar, rosemary and thyme.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Serve over linguine.
Sprinkle with Parmesan, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: edna's pound cake
directions: Separate eggs; beat egg whites until stiff.
Put in refrigerator.
Cream butter and add sugar.
Beat at high speed. Add egg yolks.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Add flavoring and fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased steeple pan.
Bake for 1 3/4 hours in a 275° oven.

title: vegetable, cracker and chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer until smooth. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving with crackers, chips or vegetables.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add orange juice.
Stir and cool in fridge.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Jell until firm.

title: muffin cones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sit ice cream cones in cups of muffin cups.
Prepare muffin mix.
Fill cones with batter.
Sprinkle some topping on each cone.
Lightly press into batter.
Bake at 400° for 23 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Preheat
oven
Grease 3 round cake pans.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl 2 minutes.
Divide batter into 3 pans.
Bake
to 25 minutes.
Cool completely and frost. Refrigerate.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs.
Add pineapple and bread cubes. Mix well. Spoon into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until light brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt in double boiler the chocolate chips, milk and sugar.
Let cool.
Beat egg yolks and add them to chocolate mixture.
Beat egg whites stiff with electric mixer.
(Hint:
This takes about 5 to 10 minutes.
Whites must stand at peaks when beaters are lifted from bowl.)
Add whites to mixture.
Add vanilla and salt.
Pour into pie crust.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt marshmallows in butter over low heat.
Stir in flavorings and food coloring.
Add cornflakes; stir well to coat.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Shape with buttered hands into wreaths.
Decorate with candies.

title: italian chicken
directions: In a small saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in tomatoes. Cover, cook over medium low heat, stirring constantly until thickened; keep warm. Combine bread crumbs and parmesan cheese. Dip chicken into crumbs, coating well. Fry chicken in oil 3 to 4 minutes on each side. Place one slice cheese on each piece of chicken. Cover and cook until melted. Place on serving plate; top with tomatoes; sprinkle with additional parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: hawaiian cream cheese cake
directions: Bake cake mix in greased and floured jelly roll pan (11 x 16-inch) at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.
Cream together cream cheese, vanilla pudding and milk.
Spread over cooled cake. Sprinkle pineapple over cream cheese mix.
Spread container of Cool Whip over pineapple.
Garnish top of Cool Whip with chopped nuts and coconut.

title: gnocchi ala romaine (french-italian)
directions: Bring milk to boil. Add the 1/2 cup butter, salt and pepper. Stir in grits and cook until thick. Beat until thick. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2 Pyrex. Chill well. Cut into oblong (domino shapes) and drop into a buttered casserole, as dominoes would fall. Put cheeses over; pour the 1/2 cup butter (melted) over. Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: dave's southern buttered beans and ham hocks
directions: Put beans, ham hocks and salt into a crock-pot.
Beans should not be much more than half full of the crock-pot.
If so take out some of the beans.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread pie filling on pizza crust.
Mix oatmeal, brown sugar and cinnamon. Crumble mixture over the pie filling.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Drizzle thin icing over top.
Serve hot.

title: mexican snack squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 4 rectangles.
Place crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking dish.
Press over bottom and 1-inch up sides.
In a small bowl, combine sour cream and taco mix.
Bake dough for 14 to 19 minutes.
Cool completely. Spread beans over crust.
Spread taco-sour cream mixture over top of beans.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: gourmet carrot casserole
directions: Note: This recipe must be made with real butter; flavors blend for its fabulous taste!

title: hurry-up chicken(yield: 6 servings)
directions: 1. Wrap 1 strip bacon around each chicken breast half.

title: toffee treats
directions: Cream
butter and sugar; add egg yolk and vanilla.
Mix well. Add
flour	and
salt.
Mix
together
into dough.	Pat dough onto the surface of a 17 x 24-inch greased cookie sheet. Bake
at
375° for
to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Put back in oven for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat, green pepper and onion.
Place layer of potatoes in baking dish, then 1/2 cream soup and layer of meat.
Add other potatoes, cream soup and remainder of meat in layers. Top with cheese slices and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Beat into eggs.
Stir in rhubarb.
Line a 9-inch pie pastry.
Fill; dot with butter.
Top with lattice crust; flute edges.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool.

title: better than sex dessert
directions: Crust:
Grease bottom 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Blend flour, butter and walnuts.
Press into pan bottom.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until golden.

title: lip smacking good
directions: In a large bowl, combine undrained fruits and lemon juice. Sprinkle instant pudding mix over fruit; toss lightly to combine. Chill.
Just before serving, add 1 1/2 cups chopped or sliced bananas.
Fold into chilled mixture.

title: clown cakes
directions: Bake cupcakes; cool and ice with yellow icing (white icing with 3 to 4 drops of yellow food coloring; stir).
Place one marshmallow on center top.
Dip bugle in red icing and place on top of marshmallow.
Make a ball of red icing and mold on the pointed end of the bugle.
Arrange 8 Good-N-Plenty around the marshmallow on top of the cake (alternate colors).
Dip toothpick in food coloring and draw a face on the marshmallow (like +'s).

title: christmas morning casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch lightly greased casserole dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° preheated oven for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in the water.
Stir
in	all, except the sour cream.
Place half of mixture in
mold
and
let
it
get firm. Spread sour cream on firm
jello.
Gently spread on the remainder of jello mixture.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: chuck roast with garlic and onions
directions: With a sharp knife, cut 10 slits in the roast; insert garlic cloves. Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper. In a Dutch oven, brown meat on both sides in the canola oil. Drain. Top roast with onion slices and bay leaves, if using. Drizzle with melted margarine. Add water to the pan, cover and bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Baste roast with pan juices; add carrots and sliced potatoes. Cover and cook an additional 45 to 60 minutes, until meat and veggies are tender. Discard bay leaves.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Pour milk and juice into a bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat at lowest speed 1 minute.
Add the Cool Whip and beat 1 more minute. Arrange in bowl in layers, half of the fruit, pudding mix, fruit, then mix.
Decorate, if desired.

title: people puppy chow(one of the most popular recipes)
directions: Melt chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter.
Mix well and pour over cereal, stirring gently.
Add cereal mixture and shake gently to coat.
Store in covered container.

title: memaw's surprise
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle graham cracker crumbs in dish.
Pat firm to form crust.
Layer coconut, chocolate chips, pecan pieces, then pour milk over top.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 24 bars.

title: fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large saucepan; stir constantly and bring to a boil over moderate heat.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add chocolate morsels until well blended, then add walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into aluminum foil lined 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Cut and store in airtight container.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; cool.
Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight or several hours.

title: layered macaroni shrimp salad
directions: In a large glass bowl, layer greens, macaroni, 1 1/2 cups of cheese, tomatoes, shrimp, peas and cabbage.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, rice, Cheez Whiz and broccoli.
Bake in large baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes. Recipe may be halved.

title: crispy cheese bites
directions: Stir together butter and cheeses until blended. Stir in flour and remaining ingredients (dough will be stiff).

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, rice, water, onion and spices. Shape into balls.
Place balls in ungreased baking pan.
Stir together remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well; bring to boil, then cook low and slow.
(Keeps well in jar in refrigerator.)

title: millionaire pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and butter together, then add 2 cups of flour and mix well.
Then add 2 more cups of flour.
Mix well.
Add milk. Mix well.
Add 1 of the eggs at a time and mix well.
Then add vanilla and lemon flavors.
Blend well and pour into a greased and floured Bundt cake pan at 350° for 35 minutes, until brown and done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; chop and spread in bottom of baking dish.
Add soup mixture.
Do not add water.
Top with crackers and margarine mixture.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Coat chicken at least an hour before cooking and handle chicken as little as possible.

title: angel macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cover cookie sheet with cooking parchment paper or aluminum foil.

title: praline crunch(serve over ice cream)
directions: Melt oleo and brown sugar in a pan.
Bring to a boil and immediately remove from heat.
Add pecans and corn flakes; toss together with a fork to coat.
Spread on waxed paper to cool. Store in airtight container.

title: fettucini alfredo with vegetables
directions: Parboil vegetables until tender (do not overcook to soft). Rinse in cold water and set aside.
In a medium saucepan, add milk and cornstarch; stir until blended over medium heat.
Add margarine and stir until margarine melts and mixture thickens and is smooth.
Add pepper and Parmesan; remove from heat. Simultaneously cook fettucini noodles according to package directions.
Rinse with cold water and place in a large bowl.
Add broccoli, cauliflower and cheese sauce.
Stir together and serve with a salad and garlic bread.

title: easy quiche
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add soup and cream, mixing well.
Sprinkle cheese, bacon and broccoli evenly over pie crust. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center is set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: party meat balls
directions: Combine meat, soup mix, bread crumbs, salt and eggs.
Form into small balls.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana fudge-walnut brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of an 8-inch square pan.
Melt in a 2 quart saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally, the margarine and chocolate chips.
Beat in thoroughly with a spoon the flour, sugar, chopped walnuts, banana, vanilla, baking powder, salt and 1 egg.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake about 30 minutes or until center is set.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: linguini
directions: In pan, simmer butter, oil, garlic, onion and parsley; add clams, juice and basil.
Simmer; never bring to boil.
To remaining juice from can of clams, add cornstarch.
Pour into mixture and stir.
Pour over cooked linguini to serve.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Mix approximately 2 tablespoons water with refried beans. Spread over round platter.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Mix and spread over refried beans.
Spread guacamole on top of sour cream mixture.
Layer next:
chopped green onions, tomatoes and olives.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top as the last layer.
Serve chilled or at room temperature with tortilla chips.

title: old-fashioned vegetable soup
directions: In large
pot,
cook beef stew until tender.
Add green beans, tomatoes, corn, peas, fresh cabbage and potatoes.
Cook on medium heat
for
about 2 hours or until all vegetables are done, stirring often.

title: great grandmother's western salad
directions: Blend 1 tablespoon peach syrup into cream cheese, mixing until fluffy.
Add finely chopped dates, chopped walnuts and grated orange rind.
Spoon onto peach half that has been chilled and drained.
Serve on greens.
Or spread peach halves with filling and top them with a second half to form a whole peach and serve. Makes enough filling for 5 to 8 peaches.

title: apple harvest squares
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, salt and 1/3 cup sugar.
Cut in oleo until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Press into the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Arrange the apple slices on top of crumbs and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: egg salad
directions: Boil eggs in salt water.
After boiled, add a little salt and pepper.
Add onions.
Mix good.
Eat with bread or eat plain.

title: overnight salad
directions: Put in a large bowl in layers as listed.
Refrigerate overnight; toss together before serving.

title: hot crab and shrimp spread
directions: Drain shrimp and artichoke hearts.
Chop artichokes.
Mix shrimp, crabmeat, artichokes, cheese and mayonnaise together. Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve on crackers.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in egg and milk.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate morsels.
Drop by level measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen 2 1/4-inch cookies.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Blend in bananas.
Stir in wafers, then pecans and raisins.
Pour batter into two greased 9-inch round pans.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Cool completely. Spread one layer with marshmallow cream and cover with second layer.
Sift powdered sugar over top.

title: n c barbecued pork
directions: Pierce pork roast.
Marinate in vinegar, pepper and salt overnight, or at least for a few hours.
Drain marinade from meat and use as basting sauce during roasting time.

When roast is done, chop into bite size pieces and place in 3-quart casserole. Boil another cup of cider vinegar, to which you may add more pepper and salt, if needed, and pour over meat in casserole.
Put in a 300° oven for 30 to 45 minutes before serving.
Pass bottled hot sauce.
Serves 6.

title: upside-down beef cornbread
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and meat into Crisco until lightly browned.
Add sauce and seasonings and let simmer while mixing cornbread mixture.
Pour batter mixture over the hot meat mixture. Bake in a 6 x 10-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn out on a platter upside down and serve.

title: marshmallow delight
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk on low.
Cool.
Add whipped cream and pineapple.
Pour over 1/2 of crushed graham crackers.
Pat down in 12 x 15-inch glass dish.
Put other 1/2 of crushed graham crackers on top.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip kiss cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove wrappers from chocolate pieces.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add flour; blend until smooth.
Stir in small chocolate chips.
Mold scant tablespoon dough around each chocolate piece, covering completely.
Shape into balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely. Drizzle topping over each cookie.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: mexican dip
directions: Fry sausage and hamburger together, then drain oil.
Combine Velveeta, hot taco and medium taco sauce; add meat into a crock-pot.
Cook on low 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with chips.

title: jello roll-ups
directions: Lightly spray 8 or 9-inch square pan with no-stick cooking spray.
Spread around with paper towel.

title: mystery cracker pie
directions: Crumble crackers fine.	Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Whip egg whites, sugar and vanilla until stiff.	Fold crumb mixture into egg whites.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip, shaved chocolate and chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes in boiling water.
Drain well. Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs, cheese, pepper to taste and onion. Mix well.
Add broccoli and spoon into a lightly greased Pyrex dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pan. Let boil 15 minutes. Fill jars. Process in a boiling water bath for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let set for 1 week.

title: crazy crust pie (cobbler)
directions: Mix. Add filling (fruit of your choice, juice and all).
Bake in 400° oven.

title: strawberry cream cake
directions: Prepare angel food cake mix according to package directions, using a 10-inch tube pan.
Invert pan on funnel or bottle for 2 hours or until cake is completely cooled.
Loosen cake from sides of pan, using small metal spatula.
Remove from pan.
Cut a 1-inch slice crosswise from top of cake and set aside.
Cut 1-inch from center hole and outer edge of cake with sharp knife.
Carefully remove center of cake, gently pulling cake pieces out with fingers, leaving a 1-inch layer of cake on bottom.
Reserve cake pieces.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add milk; mix well.
Stir in lemon juice and almond extract.
Fold in cake pieces and strawberries; spoon into tunnel in center of cake.
Top with reserved cake slices.
Chill 8 hours.
Frost with whipped topping.
tags: Betty Crocker white angel food cake mix

title: pork chops marengo
directions: Coat pork chops as directed on box.
Combine spaghetti sauce and mushrooms with liquid in a shallow baking dish.
Scatter pepper and onion (sliced) over sauce.
Arrange chops on top.
Bake 45 minutes or until done in a 425° oven.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Heat milk, sugar and cocoa to a boil, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Remove from heat after boiling for 1 minute.
Blend in margarine, vanilla and salt.
Makes 3 cups.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except hot water.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes. Stir in hot water by hand.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: southern banana nut bread
directions: Combine Crisco and sugar.
Beat in eggs, salt, bananas, flour, soda, powder and nuts.
Bake for 70 minutes in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Do not open oven door during baking.

title: dilliards cake
directions: Beat egg. Add sugar. Melt butter and cocoa together. Add milk and flour alternately. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes in two 8 x 8-inch pans. Line pans with wax paper. Allow paper to come up sides of pan. When cool, frost with the following Mocha Icing.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cut up cherries. Chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fried rice
directions: Brown hamburger and
onion
in	large
skillet.
Drain. Add margarine and shrimp.
In
a
different
bowl
beat
eggs. Remove shrimp from pan and
cook
(scramble)
eggs in same pan used for shrimp.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soy sauce with meat, shrimp, onions and eggs.
Add cold, cooked rice and simmer for 15 to 30 minutes, turning over constantly.
Add soy sauce to taste.

title: cucumber-cream cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add next four ingredients and mix well.
Stir in onion and cucumber.
Put in covered container.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: pear lime mold salad(doubled)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in pear syrup and bring to boil.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mash pears; whip with mixer.
Beat in cream cheese until smooth and add to slightly thickened gelatin.
Fold in whipped cream.
You may want to reserve some for topping.
Chill until set.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften margarine and cream cheese; blend until smooth.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add to cream mixture, about 1/3 cup at a time.
Add flavorings.
Bake in a well-greased 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a 325° oven.
Let stay in pan for 5 minutes, then turn out.
Cool on rack until cool.

title: macaroni and shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water only until just tender, then drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain again.
Chill thoroughly.
Mix chilled macaroni with celery, pimento, shrimp, onion and green pepper.
Add French dressing to coat the ingredients and marinate for at least a hour.
Drain any excess French dressing from salad and add mayonnaise to bid the ingredients together.
Pile in a lettuce lined bowl and garnish with egg slices.
Or pile into individual lettuce cups and garnish with egg slices.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well with mixer.
Roll into small balls the size of a small walnut.
Place on cookie sheet. Press each ball with bottom of glass that has been greased with butter, slightly twisting as you press down.
This will keep the glass from sticking to the dough.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cookie cool slightly.
Then dip in powdered sugar and place on a plate.
Makes 135 cookies.

title: potato chip cookies(makes 7 to 8 dozen.)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add vanilla and sifted flour.
Fold in crushed potato chips.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten down with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar after baking or you may sprinkle with colored sugar before baking for Christmas cookies or other holidays.

title: dolly madisons
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients to form crust in a 9 x 13 glass pan. Layer remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fettucini carbonara
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.
Fry bacon until crisp, drain and crumble. Cook fettucini. Drain and place in large serving dish. Add bacon, butter, cream, cheese and eggs. Toss until fettucini is well coated.

title: crisp baked fries
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Slice potatoes to suit.
Coat baking sheet with 4 sprays of oil.
Mix egg whites and Cajun spice in a bowl.
Add sliced potatoes.
Pour coated potatoes onto baking sheet.
Spread in a single layer.
Bake for 45 minutes, turning every 6 to 8 minutes.

title: ever ready fridge muffins
directions: Combine boiling water and Bran Buds; let stand.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs; add flour, salt, and soda alternately with buttermilk.
Add Bran Buds and All-Bran.
Keep in covered container in fridge for 3 to 4 weeks.
Bake as needed.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss broccoli, onion, and raisins together.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, and vinegar together.
Pour over mixture.
Add crumbled bacon just before serving.

title: applesauce - oatmeal muffins (low fat)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line muffin pan with liners (12 muffin cups).
Combine all dry ingredients.
Add applesauce, milk, oil and egg white.
Stir just until ingredients are
moistened.
Fill cups almost full.
Bake 20 - 22 minutes until golden brown.
These muffins are very moist.
They freeze well for future use.

title: caesar salad
directions: Add garlic to salad oil.
Let set for 30 minutes or more.
Add salt and pepper.
Combine lemon juice and boiled eggs.
Remove garlic clove.
Add oil to lemon juice mixture.
Toss lettuce with dressing.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Top with croutons, if desired.

title: cake topping(from kelley jo's great grandmother eldridge)
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil in saucepan, then add coconut. Spread over any kind of prepared warm cake mix (yellow, white, chocolate, etc.) and brown under broiler until coconut becomes toasty.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans and pour into 9 x 13 greased pan. Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over coconut and pecans. Heat butter and cream cheese until warm enough to stir in sugar. Once sugar is dissolved, spoon over cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Don't cut cake until cool.

title: oven barbecued spareribs
directions: Put uncut ribs in roasting pan. Place sliced lemons and onion on top of ribs. Cover and bake at 450° for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, combine the remaining ingredients in a medium saucepan. Stir and bring mixture to a boil over medium heat. Pour mixture over ribs. Reduce oven temperature to 350°. Bake 1 hour or until ribs are tender.
Baste often.

title: wine biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Spoon into unbaked tart shells and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: key lime cheese cake with strawberries(diabetic dessert)
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
Coat 9-inch spring form pan with non-stick spray and set aside.
Put graham cracker pieces and margarine in blender, pulse until coarse in texture.
Press mixture on bottom and 1/2-inch up side of pan.
Bake until light brown.
Cool on rack.
Beat cream cheese, yogurt, 6 packs sugar substitute, peel, juice and vanilla in large bowl on high speed until smooth.
Pour into cooked pie crust.
Cover with plastic wrap and freeze 2 hours or refrigerate overnight.
Combine strawberries and remaining packets of sugar 30 minutes before serving and set aside.
Just before serving spoon mixture over cheesecake.
Serves 8-10.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, add salt, pepper, and flour.
Add milk slowly and heat until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
It makes 1 cup of sauce.

title: holiday fragrance
directions: Place spices in a large kettle with pineapple juice, apple cider and water.
Bring to a boil for several minutes.
Reduce heat and simmer, allowing house to fill with a wonderful holiday fragrance.

title: terri's peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: coconut cake(in memory of kathy cody)
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake four layers or bake two layers and slice each layer into two layers.
Mix sugar, sour cream and flavoring together.
Add 1 1/2 packages of frozen coconut to sugar mixture.

title: rocky road frosting
directions: In a 2-quart heavy saucepan, combine chocolate, half the marshmallows, water and butter.
Heat until blended, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly; add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Stir in remaining marshmallows.
Add nuts.
Frosts one 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: hot chicken salad(serves 4 to 5)
directions: Combine all ingredients (except onion rings and cheese).
Mix well.
Put in ungreased casserole and top with onions and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(Can be made ahead, frozen and reheated.)

title: sally's soft pretzels
directions: Mix yeast, water, sugar and salt in bowl.
Stir in flour; knead dough.
Roll into ropes for pretzels.
Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle salt.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes, on aluminum foil or cookie sheet.

title: first cousin to german chocolate cake
directions: Blend ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour batter in 3 cake pans (8 or 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost with the German Chocolate Frosting.
You may like this recipe better than the original and it is much easier!

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Cut middle of bread out making a bowl for the dip.
Transfer dip from large bowl to bread bowl, cutting excess bread into pieces for dipping.

title: walnut pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then turn oven down to 300° or 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple sour cream cake
directions: Combine pineapple with juice and baking soda.
Mix well.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix and remaining ingredients.
Add pineapple mixture.
Blend.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Do not underbake.
Cool.
Remove from pan.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil slowly, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring over medium heat to 236°.
Remove from heat and let stand 15 minutes.
Do not stir.
Add vanilla; beat until mixture starts to lose gloss (about 8 minutes).
Stir in nuts and quickly pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in skillet.
Drain grease off beef.
Mix soups into beef and onion and stir.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover it with cheese.
Then cover with Tater Tots and bake at 350° until brown and cheese bubbles through Tater Tots.

title: easy bake kielbasa
directions: Slice kielbasa diagonally into 1-inch thick slices.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 12 x 2-inch cake pan.
Pour barbecue sauce over sausage, making sure to cover each piece.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 40 minutes or until done.
Serves 12 or more.

title: new orleans pralines
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar and soda.
Stir in cream. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir to soft ball stage (234° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat; add butter.
Stir in pecans.
Beat candy until thick enough to drop from spoon.
Drop tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
If candy becomes too stiff to drop, add a little hot water to make right consistency.
Serves 24.

title: strawberry oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together sugar and butter.
Mix in eggs, milk and applesauce.	Combine dry ingredients.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add the strawberries to the mixture. Pour batter into well-greased muffin pans.	Bake for 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 20 muffins.

title: hominy san juan
directions: Drain hominy and place in a saucepan.
Add sour cream, chilies and cheese.
Mix over low heat.
Add salt.
Place in an ungreased casserole and bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage cake
directions: Combine sugar, cloves, cinnamon, allspice, baking soda, baking powder, nutmeg, raisins, pecans, hot coffee, cherries and juice.
Mix flour with sausage.
Combine with above ingredients. Grease and flour pan.
Line with wax paper, spoon cake batter evenly.
Bake at 250 degrees for about 1-1/2 hours (check with toothpick).

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix sour cream and pineapple together well, then mix into Jell-O.
Pour into mold. Sprinkle chopped nuts over top; chill.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni, mix all ingredients and place in a greased casserole.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Combine broccoli, bacon and raisins in a large bowl with lid.
In blender combine mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and onion.
Blend until smooth. Pour over broccoli mixture and toss to coat.
Cover bowl with lid and refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.
Toss salad again before serving to coat broccoli with dressing.

title: shrimp primavera
directions: Melt
butter
in
oil.	Add
lemon
peel and garlic and simmer 1	minute.
Add zucchini and green/red peppers.
Saute for 2
to 3
minutes.
Add shrimp and mushrooms.
Remove from heat.
Place in	fridge and allow to marinate for at least 30 minutes.
Return to	stove.	Saute
mixture	until shrimp are pink (about
3 to 5 minutes).
In the last few minutes stir in salt,
pepper,
basil, parsley
and
lemon juice.	Spoon over cooked spaghetti and toss well.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: state fair peach pie
directions: Mix in saucepan the tapioca, cornstarch, brown sugar, white sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Pour filling into crust.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and dot with margarine.
Add top crust which has been pricked with fork.
Seal and flute edges.
Bake in moderate oven at 400° for 35 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: cheese knots
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix together Chex crumbs, cheese and butter.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits.
Cut each in half.
Press each half in crumb mixture to coat both sides thoroughly.
With hands, roll each piece to form an 8-inch stick. (Crumbs will work into dough.)
Gently tie to form a knot.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve immediately.

title: russian pancakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat milk, water and margarine until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add egg yolks; continue beating at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Cover; let rise until doubled, about 50 minutes.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Stir batter down.
Fold egg whites into batter; let stand 10 minutes. Pour 1/4 cup into hot, greased griddle.
Bake until puffed and bubbly; turn and bake until nicely browned.
Stir batter down occasionally.

title: quick wedding punch
directions: Mix jello and water together.
Add pineapple juice and enough water to make one gallon.
Freeze.
Set out two or three hours before and add ginger ale.
Should be slushy when served.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together except eggs.
Beat eggs and fold in mixture.
Place in greased casserole with lid.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes; turn down to 350° for 35 minutes or until puffs up. (Bake until liquid is gone at top.)

title: chopped broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain package of broccoli.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: cheesy rice and broccoli
directions: Bring water to a boil in saucepan.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir with fork until blended.
Add tomatoes and green pepper; let stand 10 minutes or to desired consistency (rice will thicken up on standing).

title: spinach pie
directions: Thaw, drain and squeeze dry spinach.
Add spinach, bread crumbs, melted butter and eggs into bowl.
Mix well.
Spread into baking dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes. Then broil until cheese is golden brown.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: old south chicken and dumplings(100 year old recipe)
directions: Cook chicken in boiling, salted water until tender.
Remove chicken from broth; skin, debone and keep warm.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix cooked Rice-A-Roni with other ingredients (except potato chips).
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° (can use crock-pot *). Sprinkle with crushed potato chips.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit dressing for red raspberry salad
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and juices.
Cook until thick.
When cool, fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on salad.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Cook at 400° until shaky, about 30 minutes. Then cook at 200° for about 15 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix together the cooked noodles, cooked and drained ground beef or turkey and sauces.
Put layer in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Repeat.
If you like, put pepperoni slices on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Will freeze.
Makes a large amount.
Can be divided into smaller casseroles.

title: cheese-green bean bake
directions: Pour beans in casserole dish. Melt butter in pan. Add flour and salt. Stir until smooth.
Add milk and heat. Stir until creamy. Add cheese. Stir until it is all melted.
Pour sauce over beans and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
(May sprinkle bread crumbs on top before baking.)

title: healthful bran muffins
directions: Cream eggs, honey and oil.
Add boiling water into Bran Buds and
raisins.
Cool.
Add
bran-water
mix to eggs, etc. Add
bran flakes.
Alternate buttermilk with sifted dry ingredients.	Bake at 350° to 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Dough may be kept in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.

title: peanut blossoms(party peanut butter cookies)
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add white sugar and brown sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and beat well.
Shape teaspoonfuls of dough into ball and roll in sugar. Bake on a greased cookie sheet in preheated 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Then remove from oven and place a chocolate candy kiss on each cookie.
Press down firmly so cookie cracks around edge. Return to oven and bake 2 to 5 minutes more until golden brown. Yields about 4 dozen cookies.

title: chili success
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
In a large saucepan, combine chili, vegetable juice and vegetables.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer over low heat for 4 or 5 minutes.
Serve over rice and top with sliced onions, sour cream and grated cheese.
Serves 4.

title: swedish kaldolmar(stuffed cabbage)
directions: Core cabbage. Pluck off leaves separately and wilt in boiling water. Season meat. Add rice and onion and mix. Form into patties and wrap in cabbage leaves. Fasten with toothpicks. Butter pan and place patties side by side so as to keep their shape while browning. Bake about 1 hour in slow oven (325°), basting occasionally with melted butter. Remove from pan. Mix 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 cup cream and add to juice in pan. Cook until smooth. Return rolls to gravy to reheat.

title: stuffed turkey roll
directions: In a bowl, combine egg, oats, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add turkey and mix well.
On wax paper, pat mixture to a 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
In saucepan, cook onion and celery in butter until tender. Stir in sage, poultry seasoning, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and dash of salt.
Toss bread cubes with mixture and 2 tablespoons water.
Spread atop meat mixture. Roll up meat, jelly-roll style, starting from narrow end. Press edge to seal.
Seal ends.
Transfer roll, seam side down, to greased baking dish. Cut bacon slices in half, crosswise, and lay atop turkey roll.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: b~b~q meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger meat, egg, onion, bell pepper, oatmeal, salt and pepper.
Add BBQ sauce to the meat mixture, mixing well.
Put in a loaf pan.
Bake for 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Remove and cover top with BBQ sauce and bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: walter's deer stew
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Slice onion thin; fry in pan.
Dice tenderloin and brown.
Add 1/2 cup of water and Kitchen Bouquet. Add tomatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Simmer until potatoes are done.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Combine raisins and vinegar in medium bowl; let stand for 15 minutes.
Add carrots and pineapple tidbits; stir well.
Combine pineapple juice, cinnamon and nutmeg; pour over carrot mixture and toss well.
Cover and chill.

title: orange roughy with dill
directions: Place 2 tablespoons of butter in microwave-safe dish or pie plate.
Microcook on High for 25 to 30 seconds or until butter is melted.
Stir in bread crumbs and microcook for 2 minutes on High, stirring after one minute.

title: diet jello salad
directions: Can be used with mayonnaise as a salad or
Cool Whip as a dessert.

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: On medium heat, melt jelly and mustard.
Drop cut up wieners in and bring to a boil.
If you want to keep them warm, put in a crock-pot.

title: quick and easy strawberry pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and press into 9X13 pan. Bake at 350° for 7 minutes and cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw and drain frozen broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° in a lightly greased casserole for less than 1 hour.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Put cabbage head in boiling water for a few minutes; set aside and drain, just enough to separate leaves.
Mix all these things together and fold into cabbage leaves.
Place sauerkraut in bottom of pan or casserole.
Add cabbage rolls on top.
Lay little small smoked sausage around through pan and sprinkle a little red pepper seeds through pan.
Pour stewed tomatoes over top of everything. Cook on top of stove slowly or bake in oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: pretzel layered salad
directions: Mix pretzels, oleo and sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add eggs, sugar, buttermilk and coconut. Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, water and cheese.
Over low heat, heat until cheese is melted.
Stir occasionally.
Add spaghetti, chicken, pepper and parsley.
Simmer on low heat for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: homemade mustard
directions: In medium bowl, combine vinegar and mustard.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix remaining ingredients with the vinegar and mustard.
Refrigerate in airtight container.
Will keep well in refrigerator for about one month.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: You will also need 30 lollipop sticks.

title: white chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces; set aside.

title: mints
directions: Mash cheese with sugar, flavoring and coloring.
Knead like pie dough if necessary.
Must be real stiff.
Take dough the size of a marble and dip in granulated sugar; press into rose molds.
Makes 75 mints.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and margarine; fold in marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate about 2 hours.	Cut into squares and serve.

title: lima fiesta
directions: Combine all.
Marinate in refrigerator 2 hours or overnight. Garnish with watercress.

title: jello surprise
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: fruitcake cookies(holiday cookies)
directions: You will need 1 large pan (dishpan size) and 1 large mixing bowl.

title: beef cabbage casserole
directions: In medium skillet, saute onion in butter until soft, but not brown.
Add beef and cook, breaking up meat, until pink is gone. In a 2-quart buttered casserole dish, layer the carrots and half of the cabbage.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add meat mixture, press down slightly and add remaining cabbage.
Add spaghetti sauce and Worcestershire sauce and mix.
Pour over top of casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Add cheese on top and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Serve with tomato slices.

title: edyth's shrimp creole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the shrimp.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cook until shrimp turns pink.
Serve over rice.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut fat off meat.
Place on wax paper.
Pound flour mixed with salt and pepper with a mallet.
Cut into bite pieces and brown in butter (melted).
Add all ingredients except sour cream.
Simmer at least 1 hour.
Just before serving, add sour cream.
Don't boil!

title: burrito bake
directions: Mix Bisquick, water and beans in greased casserole dish. Layer in rest and bake 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, garlic salt and lemon juice; mix until cream cheese is smooth, then add cream of shrimp soup. Mix until smooth. Refrigerate overnight. Next day, boil fresh or frozen shrimp until done. Cut shrimp into small pieces and add to cream cheese mixture.

title: dixie doodles
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended. Roll into walnut size balls. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl as is.
Beat 20 minutes. Place in greased tube pan or loaf pan.
Put in cold oven.
Set temperature at 350°.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pink chicken salad
directions: Heat soup to boiling point.
Add cream cheese and mix well. Mix gelatine and water and add other ingredients.
Place in square dish and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: joaney's chinese chicken wings
directions: Cut up wings.
Combine soy sauce, water and garlic powder. Place wings in baking pan.
Pour in liquid mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: s'mores
directions: For each S'more, top 1 cracker with a piece of chocolate and a marshmallow.
Place on a paper towel.
Microwave on High for 10 to 15 seconds or until marshmallow is softened.
Cover with a second graham cracker and press together slightly.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out biscuits thin.
Place apples in center and pull sides together.
Bring 7-Up, sugar, butter and cinnamon to boil; pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: sour cream apple
directions: Mix together and bake at 375°
for 25 minutes.
Then add topping.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute pepper and onion in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole
dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix butter and Crisco together.
Add sugar.
Beat eggs one at a time to mixture.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder 3 times and add to mixture.
Add frozen coconut and Angel Flake coconut.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar and egg.
Cream well.
Mix dry ingredients and add, alternating, with the sour cream (may mix in by hand).
Chill dough.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Mix flour, egg, Jell-O instant pudding and pie filling and milk; mix for 3 minutes.
Pour into baking dish.
Add large can of sliced peaches over it.
Save the juice.
Then mix cream cheese, sugar and peach juice together.
Pour over it.
Beat for 3 minutes and bake until bubbly.

title: broccoli & cheese potatoes(makes 4 servings)
directions: In medium saucepan, cook mushrooms in margarine until tender. Add Welsh rarebit and milk; cook and stir until hot.
Slit baked potatoes lengthwise; divide hot broccoli evenly among potatoes. Top with hot cheese sauce.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cabbage a la special
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Place cabbage in cold water for 1/2 hour; drain.
Steam all together.
Mash cabbage and potatoes. Place in a greased casserole dish.
Top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Chill until it starts to gel.
Drain pineapple and add to jello.
Stir in fruits and nuts.
Chill.
Can be served on lettuce.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Heat applesauce on stove (or microwave) first. Pour all ingredients
into warmed crock-pot.
Stir often.
Cook about 8 to 10 hours, uncovered. When removing, add only 2 drops of clove oil.
Seal.
Very good. Like old-fashioned apple butter cooked outside in a copper kettle.

title: seafoam lime mold
directions: Dissolve lime jello in boiling water; add cold water and lemon juice.
Gradually add to softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Chill until almost firm.
Fold in marshmallows and pineapple.
Pour into 1-quart mold; chill until firm.
Top with maraschino cherries.
Makes 6 servings.

title: red beans and rice(southern dish)
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight or from 4 to 5 hours in cold water. Drain water. Place in a pot and cover with cold water. Heat slowly.
Add seasonings with meat, onion and chopped garlic. Boil at least 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add rice.
Mix well and let steam 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ruby bedwell's castor oil cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well and use enough flour to make a dough that can be rolled.
Roll out, cut and bake in a fast oven (375°).
Two cookies are equal to a dose of castor oil.

title: e z chicken strips
directions: Cut chicken breasts into strips.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and baking powder together.
In a medium size bowl, combine milk and egg.
Beat well.
Combine the flour mixture to egg mixture, coating on all sides of chicken.
Place in large skillet with oil or shortening and deep fat until strips are all golden in color.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill and serve.

title: standard biscuits
directions: Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk and mix just until dough follows fork around bowl.
Turn out on lightly floured surface; knead gently 2 minutes.
Roll or pat 1/2-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 450°.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Melt butter; saute mushrooms until wilted.
Add scallions; saute a few minutes.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add wine and cream.
Add cheese.
Stir over low heat until sauce bubbles and thickens.
Add shrimp, flounder and scallops.
Season to taste and pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix crumbs and margarine. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: banana chocolate crepes
directions: Melt 2 teaspoons butter.
Put flour, sugar, egg, 1/3 cup milk, melted butter and salt in processor and whip until smooth.
Let stand at least 1 hour.
Melt chocolate with 2 tablespoons butter. Stir in corn syrup, 2 tablespoons milk and another pinch of salt. Bring to boil, then simmer until thick, about 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Oil a small frypan (medium-high heat).
Pour 3 tablespoons batter and swirl to coat bottom evenly.
Cook until brown; turn and brown other side.
Repeat with remaining batter.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix milk and lime juice.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour into crust.
Chill 2 hours or freeze.

title: nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and eggs well.
Add milk.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; add to creamed mixture.
Add melted butter; mix well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Yields 3 loaves.

title: hot dog soup
directions: Slice and brown hot dogs in skillet with a little oil.
Add together in soup pot sliced hot dogs, tomato juice and diced potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are soft.
(May add more tomato juice, if desired.)
Add peas.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Beat egg yolks slightly.
Beat in lemon juice and milk.
Beat in remaining ingredients until smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Place casserole into square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches, on oven rack.
Pour very hot water in deep into pan.
Bake until golden brown, 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice well.
Drain and add pineapple and chopped nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into graham cracker pie crusts.
Cover and chill.
Best if made a day ahead of time.

title: warm brownie pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking dish. Combine flour, white sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and 1/3 cup cocoa in medium bowl.
Combine milk, margarine and vanilla in measuring cup.
Stir into dry ingredients just until blended. Spoon batter evenly into prepared dish.
Combine brown sugar and remaining 1/4 cup cocoa in small bowl.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Pour boiling water over entire mixture.
Do not stir! Bake 35 to 38 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream. Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in unsalted water.
Drain and put in baking dish.
Combine soup, cheese, milk, egg and mayonnaise and pour over broccoli.
Combine cracker crumbs and butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh garden pasta
directions: Toss vegetables with hot pasta and a scant 1/4 cup olive oil. Top with fresh chopped basil and salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: pate brisse(pastry rounds)
directions: Place flour, salt and sugar in bowl of food processor.
Add butter and process for 10 seconds or until mixture resembles coarse meal. With machine running, add ice water, drop by drop.
Stop as soon as dough holds together, even if there is water left.
Divide dough in half; turn out onto 2 large pieces of plastic wrap.
Press dough into flat circle, wrap in plastic and chill for at least 1 hour or freeze for later use.
Use for any pie or tart.
Will keep for a month in the freezer.

title: fried pies
directions: Mix cinnamon with fruit.
Set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, shortening and milk.
Mix well.
Turn onto lightly floured surface.
Knead about 10 times.
Break dough into 15 to 18 balls.
Roll each ball about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in 6-inch circles.
Place about 3 tablespoons fruit on circle.
Fold in half.
Press edges together.
Fry in deep fat until brown.

title: poppy seed bundt cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add oil and mix.
Sift flour and baking soda. Mix into egg mixture alternately with milk.
Add nuts.
Stir in poppy seeds.
Bake at 350° in greased tube or bundt pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan until brown.

title: spaghetti cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch buttered pan.
Cook meat, onion and bell pepper until meat browns and vegetables are tender.
Add the spaghetti sauce and mushrooms and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Pour 1/2 mixture in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread 1/2 of rice over mixture.
Cover with chicken, then remaining rice.
Top with rest of mixture (liquid).
Sprinkle Parmesan and bake for 2 1/2 hours. During the last 1/2 hour, cover with almonds.

title: plum cake
directions: Put all ingredients into large bowl and mix well with spoon. Do not use electric mixer.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix well and add Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: rice and gravy
directions: First you get a pot.
Then you get some rice.
Then you cook the rice.
Then cut the meat.
Then you make the gravy.
Then you put the gravy and the rice together in a pot.
Then cook the meat. Then you put rice, meat and grave together.
Then it is done.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into a large saucepan.
Cover and cook over medium to low heat.
Add onion; cook and stir until transparent. Drain, discarding all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Stir in flour; cook over medium to low heat about 6 minutes or until mixture thickens
while stirring.
Spoon gravy over biscuit halves.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Whip sugar into whipping cream and fold other ingredients in. Press into loaf pan.
Store for 2 weeks in refrigerator before serving.
Cover well.

title: barbecued venison
directions: Cook the roast and onion in cooker until tender.
Take excess fat and bone out, pull apart the meat and make sure onion is in pieces.
Then pour barbecue sauce over meat.
Mix well and slow cook for about an hour.
Serve on buns.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken; cool, debone.
Put chicken back in broth (8 c.).
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat until potatoes are done.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Combine lettuce and onions. Set aside.
Fry bacon and drain. Combine salt and vinegar with grease. Bring to a boil and pour over lettuce and onions. Crumble bacon over mixture. Eat while warm.

title: black bean enchilada casserole
directions: Pour a little enchilada sauce on bottom of 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Layer 6 tortillas overlapping (can be softened in a little oil).
Spread out beans.
Sprinkle with cilantro and garlic salt.
Layer with 1 cup cheese.
Put another layer of 6 tortillas.
Pour can of green chili enchilada sauce over casserole. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of cheese, lightly covered with foil.
Bake until cheese topping is melted.

title: jam cake(family recipe)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add buttermilk, jam and preserves.
Mix well.
In three parts, add flour mixture (all dry ingredients).
Add floured nuts and raisins.
Bake in greased tube pan at 300° to 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sarah's fudge cake
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan on top of stove.
Add cocoa.
Add 1/2 cup water and let mixture get very hot to mix well.
Remove from stove.

title: grape-nuts roast
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Let stand 20 minutes. Put in greased casserole and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: green jello salad
directions: Mix jello, water, marshmallows and pineapple and juice; let congeal.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and pecans in mixer.
Add the congealed mixture and mix again.
Put back into refrigerator for 2 hours, then serve.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Dice cheese (1/2-inch dice) and finely chop onion.
Set aside. Cook pasta according to package directions.
Do not overcook! Drain pasta and return to cooking pot.
Add milk, margarine and 1/2 of the cheese cubes.
Gently stir until cheese begins to melt.
Add remaining cheese, onion and Nature's Seasons.
Stir gently, blending all ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste, then cover the pot and let stand three or four minutes.
Stir once more and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in 2 ounces butter; mix with soup, rice, milk, broccoli, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Combine crumbs, cheese and melted butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
You may add some water chestnuts to taste and/or 1 cup of small English peas.

title: spuds and dumplings
directions: Use a big kettle.
Cover diced potatoes with 3 times as much water.
Bring to a rolling boil, then leave on medium heat.
While potatoes are cooking, mix eggs, water, salt and enough flour so dumpling mixture doesn't easily fall from spoon.
Drop dumpling mixture by teaspoon into potatoes and water.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes (will be dry in middle when done).
Don't let boil too fast or dumplings will fall apart.
When done, drain.
Add sour cream and butter.
Stir.
Serves 4.

title: mexican cornbread 1
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onions and salsa.
Let it heat up, Mix cornmeal, milk, oil, eggs and corn.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, combine corn syrup, sugar, eggs, margarine, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put pecans in unbaked pie crust. Pour filling mixture over pecans.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until center is set.

title: pralines
directions: Mix first six ingredients together in a large pan and bring to a boil over high heat, stirring all the time with a wooden spoon. Then lower heat and gently boil until candy forms a hard ball in ice water (about 25 minutes, stirring most of the time).
Damp weather takes a little longer.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Stir until it thickens.
Add nuts and beat until it starts to set up.
Spoon out into paper cups or wax paper.
Let cool and serve.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with 3 cups milk until thick. Then add Cool Whip.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all the ingredients. Shape into 1-inch balls, then flatten to 1/4-inch thick. With a fork, make a crisscross pattern. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool for 2 minutes on a cookie sheet pan.

title: pizza dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in a heatproof dish (pie plate works well).
Layer pizza sauce, cheese, pepperoni and olives.
Heat in microwave or bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve hot with Fritos.

title: vegetable goulash
directions: Brown hamburger.
Cut onions and add to hamburger.
Drain off grease.
Add carrots, potatoes and tomato sauce with 1 can of water.
Cook until potatoes and carrots are tender.

title: edith's lemon meringue pie(this recipe is over 60 years old)
directions: Stir the sugar into the slightly beaten egg yolks, then add the lemon juice and grated rind.
Mix well.
Stir the flour in 1 spoonful at a time, stirring until mixture is smooth and free of lumps.
Add the cold water, then the hot water; stir well.
Place over double boiler and cook until mixture heavily coats the spoon, then stir in butter.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with meringue (whip egg whites, vanilla and sugar until stiff but not dry) and bake for 10 minutes at 350° or until meringue is golden brown.

title: sweet and sour cabbage rolls
directions: To prepare cabbage, cut out core about 1 inch down; cover cabbage with boiling water.
Boil about 10 minutes; drain.
Remove 12 large outer leaves.
Cut out any heavy rib at bottom of each leaf.
