Spread out on flat surface ready for filling.
Shred remaining cabbage coarsely and spread over bottom of a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: aunt dale's zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion five minutes and drain.
Combine soup and sour cream, stir in carrots and fold in zucchini and onion. Combine stuffing mix and margarine. Place half of stuffing mix in bottom of casserole.
Pour vegetables on top and then remaining stuffing mix.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Coat fruits and nuts with 1/2 cup flour.
Add remaining flour; fold into creamed mixture. Add flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mash down salmon (be sure the soft bones are mashed thoroughly).
Add 1/2 cup bread crumbs, mayonnaise, eggs, green pepper, onion, salt, paprika, mustard and lemon juice; mix well. Chill for several hours.
Shape salmon mixture into 12 small or 8 large croquettes.
Coat with additional bread crumbs until well covered.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat; brown croquettes on all sides.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Put first 4 ingredients into mixing bowl and mix.
Add one egg at a time, mixing and beating after each one.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix cold stuff, then hash browns.
Put 2 cups crushed corn flakes on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: amish pie dough(makes 6 pie shells)
directions: Cut flour and Crisco with pie cutter (does not have to be very fine).
Mix egg, vinegar, sugar and salt, then add to water.
Pour water mixture into flour mixture, slowly.
This is very workable and can be rerolled, if necessary.
Divide dough into 6 equal parts.
Wrap in wax paper and freeze if not used immediately.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line 24 muffin cups with fluted liners. In large bowl, mix flour, sugars, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon on low until well combined. Add bananas, eggs, milk, margarine or butter, lemon juice and vanilla. Beat until blended. Increase speed to high; beat 1 to 2 minutes or until creamy. Spoon batter into muffin cups, filling to about 2/3 full. Bake 22 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out of center clean. Immediately remove and cool. While cooling, prepare frosting. My favorite is cream cheese. Recipe to follow.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine and heat soups, seasonings, onions and broth, mixing well.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with chips, then layer of chicken, half the sauce and cheese on top.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
May be made ahead and refrigerated or frozen.

title: fruit bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each. Add sifted dry ingredients, nuts and fruit; mix well.
Spread batter into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand in pan until cool, or overnight, if desired. Cut into 3 x 1-inch bars.
Roll each bar in very fine granulated sugar.
Store in airtight container.
Will ship well, if airtight. Can be frozen.

title: johnny marsietta
directions: Cook hamburger meat and onion; drain.
Add tomato sauce, cream of mushroom soup and noodles.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish. Layer with cheese, finishing with top layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated all the way.

title: cuban picadillo
directions: Cook rice.
Brown meat in hot oil.
Add onions and garlic. Simmer a few minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer, stirring occasionally.
Picadillo should be moist, but not soupy.
Serve over rice or can use cooked noodles.

title: baked apples
directions: Bring to a boil.
Add apples.
Boil and cook until thick and apples are tender.

title: meatballs in creamy cheese sauce
directions: Mix meat, egg, bread, onion, evaporated milk and salt thoroughly.
Shape into meatballs.
Brown in pan; drain.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Let the first 4 ingredients sit for about 1 hour, then drain off real good.
Mix and pour cucumber mixture with the
last 4 ingredients.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: quick orange cake
directions: Prepare orange cake mix according to directions and bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
While cake is cooking, combine orange juice and sugar.
When cake is done, remove from oven and pour orange juice mixture over top and let soak into cake.
Serve warm.

title: bacon horseradish dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl.
Cover; refrigerate at least 1 hour to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers, chips or raw veggies.

title: red cabbage salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients for dressing.
Cut up broccoli, cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Shred or chop red cabbage. Mix together.
Add chopped green onion, frozen peas (do not thaw) and bacon bits.
Toss all well with prepared dressing.
Allow to "season" overnight.

title: alida worsley's lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix this in a saucepan and watch carefully.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and hot water; cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat.
Slowly stir half the mixture into the slightly beaten egg yolks, then beat into mixture in saucepan. Boil 1 minute longer.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat. Continue stirring until smooth.
Blend in butter, lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Cover with thick meringue.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Beat milk and egg together.
Add bread cubes and let stand 5 minutes.
Put bread mixture in meat.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well and shape into meat balls.
Brown on top of
stove or in oven.
Place in casserole dish and cover with beef gravy.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli-n-cheese
directions: Place all ingredients, except cheese, in pot.
Cook on medium heat 30 minutes; drain broccoli.
Place cheese over broccoli and simmer 5 minutes or until it melts.

title: soy sauce deer meat
directions: Combine ingredients; add thin sliced deer meat.
Soak 24 hours or longer.
The longer it soaks the better it is.

title: black walnut fudge
directions: Boil to soft ball stage the sugar, salt and sour cream.
Add butter and black walnuts.
Cool at room temperature, without stirring, until lukewarm (110°).
Beat until loses its gloss.
Add nuts.
Spread in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into pieces.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix together and form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato skins(child snack recipe)
directions: Scrub potatoes; bake at 400° (or microwave until soft).
Slice potatoes in half lengthwise; scoop pulp from skin (can use pulp for mashed potatoes).
Cut skins lengthwise into quarters.
Place skin side down on Teflon baking sheet.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes or until crisp.
Sprinkle with cheese and melt in oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and bone. Add small box of Uncle Ben's Wild Brown rice and cook till done. Add 2 c. instant white rice. Add 1 can cream of chicken soup. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: two-flavor fudge
directions: Combine first four ingredients in saucepan and bring to a full boil over moderate heat, stirring frequently.
Boil for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream, butterscotch and semi-sweet morsels.
Stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Blend in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm. Yield:
About 2 1/2 pounds.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and butter together.
Make into small balls.
Melt chocolate and wax; dip balls into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper to harden.
Store in refrigerator.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place bread cubes in a large mixing bowl.
Add the milk and apple juice and toss. Add the apples, raisins, lemon peel, cinnamon
and nutmeg to bread cubes.

title: banana-walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with Crisco.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt onto waxed paper.
Beat together sugar, shortening and vanilla at medium speed for 5 minutes until light and fluffy.
With mixer running, beat in eggs, then bananas.
By hand, stir in flour mixture alternately with buttermilk, mixing after each addition only enough to moisten dry ingredients.
(Add dry ingredients in thirds, buttermilk in two additions.)
Stir in walnuts.
Spoon batter into pan, spreading well to corners.

title: chicken palow
directions: Pressure cook for 5 minutes.
Take out chicken; drain spices and keep liquid.
Brown 1/4 onion in oil.
Add liquid; bring to boil.
(Double liquid for how many cups of rice you use).
Add chicken and rice; boil together 5 minutes, then reduce heat and cover 15 minutes.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Cut the eggplant lengthwise and scoop out the pulp with a tablespoon.
In a saucepan, cook the pulp until tender.
In a skillet, heat a small amount of butter and fry the sliced onion. In a bowl, mash the cooked eggplant and add the fried onion, egg and enough bread crumbs to thicken.
Fill the empty eggplant shells with the mixture.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over the top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Prepare gelatin as directed, less 1/4 cup water.
While gelatin thickens, combine apples, pecans, oranges, coconut and cranberries.
Add to slightly thickened gelatin.
Add lettuce around edge of bowl and garnish top to make attractive, if desired.

title: brown sugar squares
directions: Mix butter, egg and brown sugar until creamy.
Add flour, baking powder and pecans.
Line the bottom and sides of a 10 3/4 x 7-inch cake pan with aluminum foil, then grease foil with Crisco. Pour batter into pan and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake at 400° for 7 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mock ice cream
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Pour mixture over crackers and top with crackers lined in same direction as bottom crackers.
Seal and put in freezer overnight.
Then cut into sandwich size.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Pour
beans into crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir well to blend ingredients.
Cover crock-pot.
Cook for 1 hour on high.
Then
reduce
heat
to cook for 4 to 6 hours on low.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Jell-O well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in covered dish and chill several hours.

title: mexican hot relish
directions: Peel and slice or chop tomatoes.
Add chopped onions and diced peppers.
Add other ingredients and cook for 3 hours very slowly on low heat.
Stir often.
Place in jars while hot and seal. Ready to eat when it is cool.
Yields 4 pints.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Lay crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Lay 1 slice of cheese and one hot dog on each crescent roll and roll up.
Bake at 350 degrees until crescents are golden brown.

title: orange-blueberry streusel cake(low-fat)
directions: Combine sugar and next 3 ingredients in a bowl; cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Set aside.
Remove blueberries from muffin mix box.
Drain and rinse blueberries and set aside.
Combine muffin mix and next 3 ingredients in a bowl, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Pour batter into an 8-inch square baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle sugar mixture over batter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Yield:
12 servings.
Serving size 1 (2 1/2 x 2-inch) piece.
Per serving:
2 grams fat and 129 calories.
Preparation time:
9 minutes.
Cooking time:
25 minutes.

title: oven chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss.
Lightly place in baking pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes until bubbly.

title: holiday punch
directions: Thaw frozen lemonade and orange juice.	Mix in the Kool-aids, water sugar.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add the ginger ale or 7-up.
Makes four quarts.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients; pour into pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: happy day cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Beat Crisco and half the milk into them.
Then add rest of milk, vanilla and eggs. Beat well.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: half moon cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Beat in milk, flour, soda, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet (6-inch space) at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool; frost bottoms of cookies in 1/2 vanilla frosting and 1/2 chocolate frosting.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cover carrots with water and boil until tender. Drain.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Wrap bacon around water chestnut; fasten with toothpick. Bake for 30 minutes.
Drain grease off.
Mix other ingredients; pour over and bake another 30 minutes at 350°.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Put milk and butter in top of double boiler.
Add the marshmallows; heat until melted.
Pour over cracker crumbs, chopped fruits and nuts and coconut.
Mix quickly and pour into pan.
Let chill thoroughly before unmolding, then store in refrigerator.

title: coffee cake supreme
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Cream butter and sugars together until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Alternately add flour mixture and sour cream, beating after each addition until blended.
Spread batter into greased 9 x 9-inch square pan or 9 x 2-inch round pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle topping over cake and continue to bake 15 minutes longer. Serve warm.
Makes 1 cake.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg whites, together.
Beat the egg whites; fold into mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a greased dish or pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (until top is slightly browned).
Serve hot!
Leftovers may be reheated.

title: impossible pumpkin pie(lo-cal)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Mix until smooth.
Spray 9-inch pie pan with Pam.
Pour pumpkin mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool and chill.

title: mexican pork chops for 4 people
directions: Place pork chops in skillet.
Put rice on each chop.
Into tomatoes, stir onion which has been finely chopped.
Add salt, also chili powder if desired.
Pour this tomato mixture over chops and rice and bake in moderate oven or covered skillet for 1 hour.

title: greek chicken
directions: Put chicken and potatoes in a pan. Cover with olive oil.
Add garlic salt, oregano leaves, lemon juice, salt, pepper and Greek seasonings.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix
well and pour into graham cracker crust.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix everything together, except chicken.
Knead and roll out. Cut into dumplings.
Cook chicken and take off bone.
Drop dumplings into hot gruel.
After dumplings have cooked for 10 minutes, add the chicken to the dumplings.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Put chops in bottom of casserole; add remaining ingredients in layers on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coleslaw
directions: Blend salt, mustard, sugar, lemon juice and vinegar with yogurt.
Combine vegetables and tarragon leaves. Stir in dressing. Chill.

title: tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into unbaked tart shells. Can add pecans to mix, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until done.
Makes 12 tarts.

title: montreal peppered steak marinade
directions: Combine oil, soy sauce and seasoning in a large, self-closing plastic bag or glass dish.
Add steak and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: yuletide salad
directions: Arrange greens, avocado, oranges and onions on salad plate. Sprinkle with nuts.
Serve with dressing.
Preparation Time:
15 minutes.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and milk; mix well.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix with first mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Bake in bread loaf pan at 325°.
Line pans with wax paper or grease and flour.

title: sweet wienies
directions: Wrap hot dogs in bacon using toothpicks to hold together. Combine brown sugar and mustard.
Sprinkle on top of wrap-ups. Marinate overnight or at least 8 hours.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 325°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in a greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes, when toothpick comes out clean. Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: green fluff
directions: Mix Jell-O and sugar in a bowl; mix 2 tablespoons lemon juice in boiling water.
Stir to dissolve completely.
Refrigerate until nearly jelled.

title: chocolate velvet pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake pastry shell 15 minutes. Meanwhile, in heavy saucepan, over medium heat, melt chocolate with sweetened condensed milk. Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs. Add water and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into hot pastry shell. Bake 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 300° and bake 20 minutes longer or until center is set.
Cool.
Chill thoroughly. Top with whipped cream. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until onion is soft.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not cover while baking.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Melt oleo and marshmallows in double boiler.
Roll graham crackers real fine.
Mix cherries and raisins in crackers and juice.
Fold in oleo and marshmallows and knead until mixed well. Place in butter glass cake pan and put in icebox.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in 8 x 8
x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour into dish.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: glorified meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put 1 package of dry soup mix into meat.
Mix meat well.
Spread into long baking pan.
Cook for 45 minutes.
If any grease, drain off.
Fix enough potatoes to cover top of meat.
Cover potatoes with grated cheese.
Put back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: liver pate hors d'oeuvre
directions: Simmer livers in water with salt.
Let cool in stock.
Have margarine at room temperature.
Remove livers and reserve stock. Mix with mixer.
Add softened margarine and mix well.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
If a thinner consistency is desired, add little stock until satisfactory.

title: crazy cat cookies
directions: In large saucepan, mix together over low heat first 4 ingredients.
Increase heat to medium and let mixture come to a full rolling boil for 2 minutes.
Cool, then add oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well.
On a sheet of waxed paper, spoon out cookies to desired size.

title: honeycomb party mix
directions: Mix cereal, pretzels, mixed nuts, pecan halves, raisins and dates.
Melt almond bark over hot water.
Pour over 1/2 of the mix and stir until cool.
Add the remainder of the almond bark. Keep breaking the pieces apart as it cools.
Makes 2 gallons. Store, tightly covered, in a cool place, or may freeze.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli slightly less than package instructions.
Mix broccoli, egg, mayonnaise, onion, soup and cheese.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Mix stuffing with melted butter.
Sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nautilus tuna rice casserole
directions: In a large bowl combine tuna salad, cooked rice, cheese and chilies.
Blend milk and eggs together in a separate bowl.
Then gently fold into tuna/rice mixture.
Transfer all ingredients to a 1-quart casserole dish that has been lightly coated with nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° until set, approximately 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the middle comes out dry.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: overnight buffet salad
directions: Wash spinach and lettuce.
Tear into small pieces (make sure all pieces are dry and crisp).
In 13 x9-inch baking dish layer half the spinach, lettuce, peas, onion, eggs and bacon.
Repeat layers.
In small bowl mix mayonnaise, dry salad dressing mix, sour cream and yogurt.
Spread on top of salad, making sure edges are covered.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: treasure chest bars
directions: Cream together butter and sugars; blend in eggs and teaspoon of vanilla flavoring.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add alternately with 3/4 cup milk.
Beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Add cherries and chocolate chips.
Spread in greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar frosting.

title: cranberry jelly(fun for thanksgiving and christmas)
directions: Wash 4 cups
cranberries
well.
Boil
2 cups water and pour over cranberries
in
cooking
pot.
Let
come to a boil, covered. Reduce heat
and boil slowly for 20 minutes, mashing and stirring.
Mash
through
wire strainer to remove seed and skins. Boil pulp and
juice for 3 minutes covered.
Stir in 2 cups sugar and bring
to
a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove heavy skum and pour into mold (2 quart mold).

title: hamburger potato hot dish
directions: Brown meat very lightly.
Blend with potatoes, soups and seasonings.
Mix lightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peachy cobbler
directions: Arrange drained peaches in 10-ounce square pan.
Pour on lemon juice.
Spread brown sugar over peaches.
Sprinkle on cinnamon. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and beat until smooth (will be thin).
Pour over peaches.
Drizzle margarine over batter.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: boogar hollow buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, buttermilk, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Fold in butter.
Add in vanilla. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes (until knife comes out clean).

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Saute garlic in oleo in small pan until tender.
Stir in cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Add milk, stirring well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 2 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Remove sauce and set aside.

title: deviled ham and cheese ball
directions: In small bowl, beat cream cheese, ham and mustard.
Stir in Cheddar cheese and chives.
Shape into ball.
Roll in nuts and parsley.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: amy's pork tenderloin(stuffed rolls)
directions: Combine all ingredients except water.
With a very sharp knife, cut a hole in the middle of tenderloin and stuff the mixture inside.
Heat butter in a skillet and cook tenderloin on all sides until golden brown, then put in the oven at 375° for about 30 to 40 minutes until done.
Cut into thin slices and serve.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon over 2 to 3 pounds of chicken.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Fix macaroni and cheese according to the box directions.
Add mushroom soup.
Brown ground beef in skillet and drain off grease. Add onion and bell pepper.
Mix all ingredients together and serve hot.

title: baby bottom wipes
directions: You will need one container; can use an old baby wipe container or Rubbermaid Serin Saver (approximately 6 1/2 x 6 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch); holds 5 cups.

title: pasta picante(fettuccine with vegetable sauce)
directions: In a large frying pan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and set aside.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons of the fat from the pan.
Add garlic and the onion; cook until translucent.
Add the zucchini and peppers; stir over medium-high heat until tender-crisp, about 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and green chilies, basil, parsley and oil.
Cook, stirring frequently, until hot.
Add salt.
In heated serving bowl, toss fettuccine with vegetables and bacon; sprinkle with Parmesan and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange cookies
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Cream sugar, margarine and eggs together.
Add flour and baking powder and 1 cup sour milk to which baking soda has been added (alternate mixing flour and milk to make easier).
Add juice and rind of large orange. Drop by spoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned; cool.
Ice with juice and rind of 1 large orange and 2 cups confectioners sugar.

title: velvety cocoa cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Boil until thick.
Pour into pie shell. Top with whipped cream.

title: fudge frosting
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, cream, chocolate, corn syrup and salt.
Heat slowly, stirring until dissolved.
Cook to soft ball stage (234°).
Do not stir while cooking.
Remove from heat; add butter.
Cool to lukewarm by setting in a pan of cold water. Add vanilla; beat until frosting begins to thicken and loses its gloss.
If necessary, thin with a few drops of cream.
Spread on yellow cake layers.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Roll a biscuit into a rope; bring ends together and seal.
Repeat with remaining biscuits.
Dip each circle in the melted butter, then in the cinnamon-sugar mixture. Twist circles into figure eights.
Place on greased baking sheet. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: viennese jam-filled cookies(rich, luscious sandwich cookies)
directions: In a medium bowl combine flour and baking powder.
Set aside. In a large bowl cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in ground almonds and lemon juice.
Gradually stir in flour mixture just until dough is smooth and forms a ball.
Shape in two 2-inch diameter rolls.
Wrap tight.
Chill 4 hours or until firm.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Mix sugar, flour and all other ingredients together.
Cook over slow heat.
Stir constantly until thick.
Cool and spread on cake layers.

title: old-fashioned stack cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour.
Measure with dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Divide into 6 or 7 parts. Roll out mixture on a well-floured board or pat in well-greased 9-inch pans.
Bake at 450° until slightly brown, 10 to 20 minutes. Spread each layer with filling.
Let stand in covered container at least 12 hours before cutting.

title: dorothy's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except last 2 items.
Put in greased loaf pan. Top with bacon and paprika.

title: tin plate special
directions: Wash beans. Cover with cold water and soak overnight. Bring beans to a boil and cook 1 hour. Drain and discard water. Brown roast in butter in a large Dutch oven. Add peppers and onions and cook until tender. Add beans and remaining ingredients. Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours or longer. Check at 3 hours to see if beans are tender and meat is done.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix this together in the morning.
Bake at noon time.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: Beat the cream cheese, butter and vanilla until fluffy. Gradually add the sugars and beat just enough to combine. Stir in the chocolate chips. Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours. Place the cheese mixture on a large piece of plastic wrap and shape into a ball. Refrigerate again for about an hour. Before serving, roll in pecans. Serve with graham crackers.

title: nunn better biscuits
directions: Sift flour and then measure.
Cut shortening into flour with a fork.
Add milk to make a sweet dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured board and knead gently 1/2 minute.
Roll dough out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut biscuits out.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken, skin, debone and place pieces of cut up chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chicken broth, soup, veggies and peas over medium heat; pour over chicken.
Mix together flour, buttermilk, margarine and soda.
Pour on top and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding with only 1/2 the amount of milk.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread over 9 x 13-inch pan lined with graham crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Heat icing in microwave 45 seconds.
Spread over top layer of crackers.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: an excellent dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Sear roast on all sides in 1 tablespoon hot oil. Combine all the other ingredients in a crock-pot. Transfer roast to crock-pot and slice another onion on top. Sprinkle with black pepper. Cook all day.

title: beat and eat frosting
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in bowl and add boiling water.
Beat until frosting stands in peak.
Beat about 15 minutes.
Add vanilla.

title: date nut ball
directions: Add first 4 ingredients and cook together 10 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Roll into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie pan 2/3 full of apples.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over top of apples.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over apples.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (at least 40 minutes). Delicious served warm with ice cream.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Combine
liquids;
add
dry
ingredients
and mix until moist. Fill
greased
muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Add fruit or nuts to batter, if desired.

title: no-bake fruit cake
directions: *Note:
I use cherries.
For mixed fruit I use homemade watermelon or apple preserves.

title: strawberry patch cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on the box and bake 10 minutes in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.

title: apple brandy praline pie
directions: Prepare Praline Topping; set aside.
In large bowl combine sugar, flour and salt.
Beat in eggs, corn syrup, margarine and brandy.
Stir in apples.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake in 350° oven 45 to 50 minutes or until puffed and set.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: tamale pie pronto
directions: Pour drained hominy into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread can of chili over hominy.
Spread tomato sauce over chili.
Spread 3/4 of green onions (chopped) over tomato sauce.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over all.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 of chopped green onions over cheese. Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: cowboy's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda together.
Cut in shortening (butter).
Add raisins.
Add eggs to milk and beat together.
Add this mixture to dry ingredients.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Combine flour and salt; set aside.
Mix candy, dates, nuts and coconut.
Put 1/2 cup flour over this mixture.
Mix butter, sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Add soda and buttermilk.
Add flour and fruit mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Mix orange juice and confectioners sugar.
Pour over hot cake.
Let sit overnight.

title: baked peas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place drained peas in a baking dish and add milk.
Fry salt bacon and pour over peas.
Add pimentos, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake until it bubbles. Serves 4.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add water, if needed, for easier mixing.
Roll into small balls.
Bake until brown. Excellent to make ahead and freeze.

title: minced beef chiarello
directions: Combine meat, garlic and mushrooms and saute until meat is browned and mushrooms are soft.
Add sherry (if desired), salt and pepper and continue to saute for 15 minutes, stirring frequently. Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: curried ham salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in refrigerator a few hours before serving.

title: old-fashioned fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Stir in milk and margarine and place on stove.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes for fudge and 1 minute for icing.
Place in cold water to cool and beat with mixer until cool and shiny in texture.
Add nuts and vanilla. Pour into buttered pan and cut into squares.

title: royal icing
directions: Thick icing:
In large bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar with mixer until frothy.
Gradually add powdered sugar and beat 5 to 7 minutes until glossy, stiff peaks form when beaters are lifted.

title: red beans and rice
directions: In a large stockpot put the okra, red beans, tomato sauce, diced tomatoes, crushed tomatoes, mushrooms, garlic Creole seasoning, tabasco, Worcestershire sauce, thyme, parsley flakes, pepper and 1 can of chicken broth.
Cover and place over low heat. When mixture starts to simmer add the sliced smoked sausage.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream
shortening
and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well
after
each addition.
Beat at high speed for 10 minutes.
Add
flour,
baking
powder, salt, coconut flavoring and milk.
Fold
in coconut and place in a cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: cherry o cream cheese pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and milk together until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour ingredients into pie shell and garnish with fruit toppings.
Chill for at least 2 hours.

title: vegetable and sausage soup
directions: Mix onion, potatoes, string beans and cooked sausage in 3-quart saucepan with 1 quart of water (if needed, add more) and bring to a boil.
Spoon in dumplings and simmer for 20 minutes. Very good.

title: sunday ham barbecue
directions: Brown meat in small amount of margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer at least 1/2 hour with lid on.
Remove lid and simmer until liquid is thickened.
Serve in hamburger buns. May be made ahead and stored in refrigerator.
Also may be frozen.

title: pineapple nut bread or roll
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Bake in a number 2 can or loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Very good!

title: dead man's dip
directions: Cook hamburg.
Drain well.
Add beans, salsa and cheese and simmer.
Sprinkle olives on top, if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: creamy shrimp scampi fettucine
directions: Marinate shrimp, oil, margarine, 1/4 cup wine, lemon juice, scallions, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper for 2 hours.
Remove shrimp from liquid.
In a saucepan, heat liquid ingredients and add flour and stir for 4 minutes.
Stir in rest of wine and milk and add shrimp; cook for 5 minutes, until shrimp is done.
Cook fettucine noodles and drain.
Serve Creamy Shrimp Scampi over fettucine.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate over simmering water.
Beat in softened butter, egg yolks, rum and vanilla with wire whisk. Remove from heat and refrigerate until firm enough to handle (1 hour), keeping tightly covered.
Combine cocoa and confectioners sugar.
Shape chocolate mixture into 1-inch balls and roll in cream and sugar.
Store in airtight container and refrigerate.

title: lisa's luscious buffalo wings
directions: Deep fry wings in hot grease until crispy dark brown.
Heat butter, 2 cups hot sauce, brown sugar and barbecue sauce.
Pour sauce over wings and shake until all wings are covered.
Serve with Blue cheese dip.
Pig out!

title: texas jack rice
directions: Mix rice and sour cream together.
In a buttered casserole dish, put a layer of rice mixture.
Top with a layer of cheese. Dot with butter.
Continue to layer ingredients in casserole until all are used.
Top with a layer of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: melting moments
directions: Combine flour, cornstarch and 10x sugar on wax paper.
Beat margarine in a large bowl at medium speed on electric mixer until fluffy.
Add flour mixture, beating until thoroughly combined. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place about 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets; flatten with lightly floured fork.
Bake in a slow oven (300°) for 20 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Cream together eggs and sugar.
Stir in melted margarine.
Add vanilla, vinegar and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set.
Use deep shell pie shell.
Very rich, but good.
